{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","code":"LUK","content":["- Berean Study Bible"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Luke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Luke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Luke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Luke"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Luke"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Dedication to Theophilus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Acts 1:1–3)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Many have undertaken to compose an account of the things that have been fulfilled among us,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"just as they were handed down to us by the initial eyewitnesses and servants of the word.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Therefore, having carefully investigated everything from the beginning, it seemed good also to me to write an orderly account for you, most excellent Theophilus,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"so that you may know the certainty of the things you have been taught."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Gabriel Foretells John’s Birth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"In the time of Herod king of Judea there was a priest named Zechariah, who belonged to the priestly division of Abijah, and whose wife Elizabeth was a descendant of Aaron.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Both of them were righteous in the sight of God, walking blamelessly in all the commandments and decrees of the Lord.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"But they had no children, because Elizabeth was barren, and they were both well along in years."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"One day while Zechariah’s division was on duty and he was serving as priest before God,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"he was chosen by lot, according to the custom of the priesthood, to enter the temple of the Lord and burn incense.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"And at the hour of the incense offering, the whole congregation was praying outside."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Just then an angel of the Lord appeared to Zechariah, standing at the right side of the altar of incense.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"When Zechariah saw him, he was startled and gripped with fear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But the angel said to him, “Do not be afraid, Zechariah, because your prayer has been heard. Your wife Elizabeth will bear you a son, and you are to give him the name John.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"He will be a joy and delight to you, and many will rejoice at his birth,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"for he will be great in the sight of the Lord. He shall never take wine or strong drink, and he will be filled with the Holy Spirit even from his mother’s womb.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Many of the sons of Israel he will turn back to the Lord their God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And he will go on before the Lord in the spirit and power of Elijah, to turn the hearts of the fathers to their children",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:17"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Malachi 4:5–6"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and the disobedient to the wisdom of the righteous—to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“How can I be sure of this?” Zechariah asked the angel. “I am an old man, and my wife is well along in years.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"“I am Gabriel,” replied the angel. “I stand in the presence of God, and I have been sent to speak to you and to bring you this good news.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"And now you will be silent and unable to speak until the day this comes to pass, because you did not believe my words, which will be fulfilled at their proper time.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Meanwhile, the people were waiting for Zechariah and wondering why he took so long in the temple.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"When he came out and was unable to speak to them, they realized he had seen a vision in the temple. He kept making signs to them but remained unable to speak.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"And when the days of his service were complete, he returned home."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"After these days, his wife Elizabeth became pregnant and for five months remained in seclusion. She declared,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"“The Lord has done this for me. In these days He has shown me favor and taken away my disgrace among the people.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Gabriel Foretells Jesus’ Birth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"In the sixth month, God sent the angel Gabriel to a town in Galilee called Nazareth,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"to a virgin pledged in marriage to a man named Joseph, who was of the house of David. And the virgin’s name was Mary.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"The angel appeared to her and said, “Greetings,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:28"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Rejoice"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"you who are highly favored! The Lord is with you.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:28"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Blessed are you among women!"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Mary was greatly troubled at his words and wondered what kind of greeting this might be.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"So the angel told her, “Do not be afraid, Mary, for you have found favor with God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Behold, you will conceive and give birth to a son, and you are to give Him the name Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"He will be great and will be called the Son of the Most High. The Lord God will give Him the throne of His father David,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"and He will reign over the house of Jacob forever. His kingdom will never end!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"“How can this be,” Mary asked the angel, “since I am a virgin?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"The angel replied, “The Holy Spirit will come upon you, and the power of the Most High will overshadow you. So the Holy One to be born",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["born of you"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"will be called the Son of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Look, even Elizabeth your relative has conceived a son in her old age, and she who was called barren is in her sixth month.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"For no word from God will ever fail.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:37"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["For nothing will be impossible with God."]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"“I am the Lord’s servant,” Mary answered. “May it happen to me according to your word.” Then the angel left her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Mary Visits Elizabeth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"In those days Mary got ready and hurried to a town in the hill country of Judah,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"where she entered the home of Zechariah and greeted Elizabeth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"When Elizabeth heard Mary’s greeting, the baby leaped in her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Spirit.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"In a loud voice she exclaimed, “Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"And why am I so honored, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"For as soon as the sound of your greeting reached my ears, the baby in my womb leaped for joy.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Blessed is she who has believed that the Lord’s word to her will be fulfilled.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Mary’s Song"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(1 Samuel 2:1–11)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Then Mary said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“My soul magnifies the Lord,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"and my spirit rejoices in God my Savior!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"For He has looked with favor on the humble state of His servant."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["From now on all generations will call me blessed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"For the Mighty One has done great things for me."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Holy is His name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"His mercy extends to those who fear Him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from generation to generation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"He has performed mighty deeds with His arm;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He has scattered those who are proud"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the thoughts of their hearts."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"He has brought down rulers from their thrones,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but has exalted the humble."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"He has filled the hungry with good things,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but has sent the rich away empty."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"He has helped His servant Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["remembering to be merciful,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"as He promised to our fathers,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to Abraham and his descendants forever.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"Mary stayed with Elizabeth for about three months and then returned home."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Birth of John the Baptist"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"When the time came for Elizabeth to have her child, she gave birth to a son.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"Her neighbors and relatives heard that the Lord had shown her great mercy, and they rejoiced with her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"On the eighth day, when they came to circumcise the child, they were going to name him after his father Zechariah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"But his mother replied, “No! He shall be called John.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"They said to her, “There is no one among your relatives who bears this name.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"So they made signs to his father to find out what he wanted to name the child."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"Zechariah asked for a tablet and wrote, “His name is John.” And they were all amazed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"Immediately Zechariah’s mouth was opened and his tongue was released, and he began to speak, praising God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65"},"All their neighbors were filled with awe, and people throughout the hill country of Judea were talking about these events.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66"},"And all who heard this wondered in their hearts and asked, “What then will this child become?” For the Lord’s hand was with him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Zechariah’s Song"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67"},"Then his father Zechariah was filled with the Holy Spirit and prophesied:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68"},"“Blessed be the Lord, the God of Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because He has visited and redeemed His people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69"},"He has raised up a horn of salvation for us"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the house of His servant David,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70"},"as He spoke through His holy prophets,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["those of ages past,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71"},"salvation from our enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and from the hand of all who hate us,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"72"},"to show mercy to our fathers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to remember His holy covenant,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"73"},"the oath He swore to our father Abraham,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to grant us",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"74"},"deliverance from hostile hands,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that we may serve Him without fear,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"75"},"in holiness and righteousness before Him"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["all the days of our lives."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"76"},"And you, child, will be called"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a prophet of the Most High;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["for you will go on before the Lord"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to prepare the way for Him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"77"},"to give to His people the knowledge of salvation"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["through the forgiveness of their sins,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"78"},"because of the tender mercy of our God,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by which the Dawn",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:78"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Morning Light"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Sunrise"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"will visit us from on high,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"79"},"to shine on those who live in darkness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and in the shadow of death,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to guide our feet"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into the path of peace.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"80"},"And the child grew and became strong in spirit;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:80"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["in the Spirit"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and he lived in the wilderness until the time of his public appearance to Israel."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Birth of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 1:18–25)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now in those days a decree went out from Caesar Augustus that a census should be taken of the whole empire.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["of the whole land"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["of the whole world"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"This was the first census to take place while",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["This was the census before"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Quirinius was governor of Syria.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"And everyone went to his own town to register."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So Joseph also went up from Nazareth in Galilee to Judea, to the city of David called Bethlehem, since he was from the house and line of David.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"He went there to register with Mary, who was pledged to him in marriage and was expecting a child."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"While they were there, the time came for her Child to be born.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And she gave birth to her firstborn, a Son. She wrapped Him in swaddling cloths and laid Him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Shepherds and the Angels"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And there were shepherds residing in the fields nearby, keeping watch over their flocks by night.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Just then an angel of the Lord stood before them, and the glory of the Lord shone around them, and they were terrified.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But the angel said to them, “Do not be afraid! For behold, I bring you good news of great joy that will be for all the people:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Today in the city of David a Savior has been born to you. He is Christ the Lord!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And this will be a sign to you: You will find a baby wrapped in swaddling cloths and lying in a manger.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"And suddenly there appeared with the angel a great multitude of the heavenly host, praising God and saying:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“Glory to God in the highest,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and on earth peace to men"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["on whom His favor rests!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When the angels had left them and gone into heaven, the shepherds said to one another, “Let us go to Bethlehem and see this thing that has happened, which the Lord has made known to us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"So they hurried off and found Mary and Joseph and the Baby, who was lying in the manger.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"After they had seen the Child, they spread the message they had received about Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"And all who heard it were amazed at what the shepherds said to them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But Mary treasured up all these things and pondered them in her heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"The shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all they had heard and seen, which was just as the angel had told them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Presented at the Temple"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"When the eight days before His circumcision had passed, He was named Jesus, the name the angel had given Him before He was conceived."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"And when the time of purification according to the Law of Moses was complete, His parents brought Him to Jerusalem to present Him to the Lord",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"(as it is written in the Law of the Lord: “Every firstborn male shall be consecrated to the Lord”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 13:2"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"),",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"and to offer the sacrifice specified in the Law of the Lord: “A pair of turtledoves or two young pigeons.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 12:8"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Prophecy of Simeon"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Now there was a man in Jerusalem named Simeon, who was righteous and devout. He was waiting for the consolation of Israel, and the Holy Spirit was upon him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"The Holy Spirit had revealed to him that he would not see death before he had seen the Lord’s Christ.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Led by the Spirit, he went into the temple courts.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the temple"]},"; also in verse 46"]}],"caller":"+"},"And when the parents brought in the child Jesus to do for Him what was customary under the Law,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Simeon took Him in his arms and blessed God, saying:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"“Sovereign Lord, as You have promised,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You now dismiss Your servant in peace."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For my eyes have seen Your salvation,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"which You have prepared in the sight of all people,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"a light for revelation to the Gentiles,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and for glory to Your people Israel.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"The Child’s father and mother were amazed at what was spoken about Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Then Simeon blessed them and said to His mother Mary:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, this Child is appointed to cause"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the rise and fall of many in Israel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to be a sign that will be spoken against,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"so that the thoughts of many hearts will be revealed—"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and a sword will pierce your soul as well.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Prophecy of Anna"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"There was also a prophetess named Anna, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Asher, who was well along in years. She had been married for seven years,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"and then was a widow to the age of eighty-four.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:37"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["was a widow for eighty-four years"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"She never left the temple, but worshiped night and day, fasting and praying."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Coming forward at that moment, she gave thanks to God and spoke about the Child to all who were waiting for the redemption of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Return to Nazareth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 2:19–23)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"When Jesus’ parents had done everything required by the Law of the Lord, they returned to Galilee, to their own town of Nazareth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"And the Child grew and became strong.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:40"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["became strong in spirit"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"He was filled with wisdom, and the grace of God was upon Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Boy Jesus at the Temple"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Every year His parents went to Jerusalem for the Feast of the Passover.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"And when He was twelve years old, they went up according to the custom of the Feast."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"When those days were over and they were returning home, the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem, but His parents were unaware He had stayed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Assuming He was in their company, they traveled on for a day before they began to look for Him among their relatives and friends."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"When they could not find Him, they returned to Jerusalem to search for Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Finally, after three days they found Him in the temple courts, sitting among the teachers, listening to them and asking them questions.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"And all who heard Him were astounded at His understanding and His answers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"When His parents saw Him, they were astonished. “Child, why have You done this to us?” His mother asked. “Your father and I have been anxiously searching for You.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"“Why were you looking for Me?” He asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Did you not know that I had to be in My Father’s house",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:49"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["I had to be about My Father’s business"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"But they did not understand the statement He was making to them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"Then He went down to Nazareth with them and was obedient to them. But His mother treasured up all these things in her heart."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"And Jesus grew in wisdom and stature, and in favor with God and man."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Mission of John the Baptist"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 40:1–5; Matthew 3:1–12; Mark 1:1–8; John 1:19–28)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, while Pontius Pilate was governor of Judea, Herod tetrarch of Galilee, his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea and Trachonitis, and Lysanias tetrarch of Abilene,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"during the high priesthood of Annas and Caiaphas, the word of God came to John son of Zechariah in the wilderness."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"He went into all the region around the Jordan, preaching a baptism of repentance for the forgiveness of sins,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"as it is written in the book of the words of Isaiah the prophet:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A voice of one calling in the wilderness,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘Prepare the way for the Lord,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["make straight paths for Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Every valley shall be filled in,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and every mountain and hill made low."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The crooked ways shall be made straight,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the rough ways smooth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And all humanity will see God’s salvation.’”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["And all flesh will see God’s salvation"]},";",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 40:3–5"]},"(see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then John said to the crowds coming out to be baptized by him, “You brood of vipers, who warned you to flee from the coming wrath?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Produce fruit, then, in keeping with repentance. And do not begin to say to yourselves, ‘We have Abraham as our father. ’For I tell you that out of these stones God can raise up children for Abraham.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"The axe lies ready at the root of the trees, and every tree that does not produce good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"The crowds asked him, “What then should we do?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"John replied, “Whoever has two tunics should share with him who has none, and whoever has food should do the same.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Even tax collectors came to be baptized. “Teacher,” they asked, “what should we do?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"“Collect no more than you are authorized,” he answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then some soldiers asked him, “And what should we do?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do not take money by force or false accusation,” he said. “Be content with your wages.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"The people were waiting expectantly and were all wondering in their hearts if John could be the Christ.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"John answered all of them: “I baptize you with water,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["in water"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"but One more powerful than I will come, the straps of whose sandals I am not worthy to untie.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Acts 13:25"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"He will baptize you with the Holy Spirit and with fire.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["in the Holy Spirit and in fire"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"His winnowing fork is in His hand to clear His threshing floor and to gather the wheat into His barn; but He will burn up the chaff with unquenchable fire.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"With these and many other exhortations, John proclaimed the good news to the people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"But when he rebuked Herod the tetrarch regarding his brother’s wife Herodias and all the evils he had done,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Herod added this to them all: He locked John up in prison."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Baptism of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 3:13–17; Mark 1:9–11; John 1:29–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"When all the people were being baptized, Jesus was baptized too. And as He was praying, heaven was opened,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"and the Holy Spirit descended on Him in a bodily form like a dove. And a voice came from heaven: “You are My beloved Son; in You I am well pleased.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Genealogy of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Ruth 4:18–22; Matthew 1:1–17)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Jesus Himself was about thirty years old when He began His ministry."]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He was regarded as the son of Joseph,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Heli,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"the son of Matthat, the son of Levi, the son of Melchi,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Jannai, the son of Joseph,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"the son of Mattathias, the son of Amos, the son of Nahum,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Esli, the son of Naggai,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"the son of Maath, the son of Mattathias, the son of Semein,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Josech, the son of Joda,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"the son of Joanan, the son of Rhesa, the son of Zerubbabel,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Shealtiel, the son of Neri,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"the son of Melchi, the son of Addi, the son of Cosam,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Elmadam, the son of Er,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"the son of Joshua, the son of Eliezer, the son of Jorim,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Matthat, the son of Levi,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"the son of Simeon, the son of Judah, the son of Joseph,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Jonam, the son of Eliakim,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"the son of Melea, the son of Menna, the son of Mattatha,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Nathan, the son of David,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"the son of Jesse, the son of Obed, the son of Boaz,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Sala,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:32"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Salmon"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Ruth 4:20–21"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 1:4–5"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"the son of Nahshon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"the son of Amminadab, the son of Admin,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Aram"]},"; others ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Ram"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Ruth 4:19"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 1:3–4"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"the son of Arni,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH, BYZ, and TR do not include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the son of Arni"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Hezron, the son of Perez, the son of Judah,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"the son of Jacob, the son of Isaac, the son of Abraham,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Terah, the son of Nahor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"the son of Serug, the son of Reu, the son of Peleg,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Eber, the son of Shelah,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"the son of Cainan, the son of Arphaxad, the son of Shem,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Noah, the son of Lamech,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"the son of Methuselah, the son of Enoch, the son of Jared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of Mahalalel, the son of Cainan,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"the son of Enosh,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["En&#333;s"]},", a variant spelling of Enosh; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Genesis 5:6"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"the son of Seth, the son of Adam,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the son of God."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Temptation of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 4:1–11; Mark 1:12–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then Jesus, full of the Holy Spirit, returned from the Jordan and was led by the Spirit into the wilderness,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["in the wilderness"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"where for forty days He was tempted by the devil. He ate nothing during those days, and when they had ended, He was hungry."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The devil said to Him, “If You are the Son of God, tell this stone to become bread.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It is written: ‘Man shall not live on bread alone.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 8:3"]},"; BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["on bread alone, but on every word of God"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then the devil led Him up to a high place and showed Him in an instant all the kingdoms of the world.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“I will give You authority over all these kingdoms and all their glory,” he said. “For it has been relinquished to me, and I can give it to anyone I wish.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So if You worship me, it will all be Yours.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It is written: ‘Worship the Lord your God and serve Him only.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:8"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:13"]},"; BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["“Get behind Me, Satan! For it is written..."]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then the devil led Him to Jerusalem and set Him on the pinnacle of the temple. “If You are the Son of God,” he said, “throw Yourself down from here.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For it is written:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘He will command His angels concerning You"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to guard You carefully,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and they will lift You up in their hands,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that You will not strike Your foot against a stone.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 91:11–12"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It also says, ‘Do not put the Lord your God to the test.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:16"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When the devil had finished every temptation, he left Him until an opportune time."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Begins His Ministry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 9:1–7; Matthew 4:12–17; Mark 1:14–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Jesus returned to Galilee in the power of the Spirit, and the news about Him spread throughout the surrounding region.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"He taught in their synagogues and was glorified by everyone."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Rejection at Nazareth"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 61:1–11; Matthew 13:53–58; Mark 6:1–6)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then Jesus came to Nazareth, where He had been brought up. As was His custom, He entered the synagogue on the Sabbath. And when He stood up to read,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"the scroll of the prophet Isaiah was handed to Him. Unrolling it, He found the place where it was written:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"“The Spirit of the Lord is on Me,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["because He has anointed Me"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to preach good news to the poor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He has sent Me to proclaim liberty to the captives",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:18"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["He has sent Me to heal the brokenhearted, to proclaim liberty to the captives"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and recovery of sight to the blind,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["to release the oppressed,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"to proclaim the year of the Lord’s favor.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:19"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to proclaim the acceptable year of the Lord"]},";",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 61:1–2"]},"(see also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then He rolled up the scroll, returned it to the attendant, and sat down. The eyes of everyone in the synagogue were fixed on Him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"and He began by saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Today this Scripture is fulfilled in your hearing.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"All spoke well of Him and marveled at the gracious words that came from His lips. “Isn’t this the son of Joseph?” they asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Surely you will quote this proverb to Me: ‘Physician, heal yourself! Do here in Your hometown what we have heard that You did in Capernaum..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then He added,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Truly I tell you, no prophet is accepted in his hometown.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But I tell you truthfully that there were many widows in Israel in the time of Elijah, when the sky was shut for three and a half years and great famine swept over all the land.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Yet Elijah was not sent to any of them, but to the widow of Zarephath in Sidon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And there were many lepers",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["leper"]},"was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"in Israel in the time of Elisha the prophet. Yet not one of them was cleansed—only Naaman the Syrian.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"On hearing this, all the people in the synagogue were enraged.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"They got up, drove Him out of the town, and led Him to the brow of the hill on which the town was built, in order to throw Him over the cliff.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But Jesus passed through the crowd and went on His way."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Expels an Unclean Spirit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 1:21–28)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then He went down to Capernaum, a town in Galilee, and on the Sabbath He began to teach the people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"They were astonished at His teaching, because His message had authority."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"In the synagogue there was a man possessed by the spirit of an unclean demon. He cried out in a loud voice,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"“Ha! What do You want with us, Jesus of Nazareth? Have You come to destroy us? I know who You are—the Holy One of God!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But Jesus rebuked the demon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Be silent!” He said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Come out of him!” At this, the demon threw the man down before them all and came out without harming him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"All the people were overcome with amazement and asked one another, “What is this message? With authority and power He commands the unclean spirits, and they come out!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"And the news about Jesus spread throughout the surrounding region."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals at Peter’s House"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 8:14–17; Mark 1:29–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"After Jesus had left the synagogue, He went to the home of Simon, whose mother-in-law was suffering from a high fever. So they appealed to Jesus on her behalf,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"and He stood over her and rebuked the fever, and it left her. And she got up at once and began to serve them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"At sunset, all who were ill with various diseases were brought to Jesus, and laying His hands on each one, He healed them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Demons also came out of many people, shouting, “You are the Son of God!” But He rebuked the demons and would not allow them to speak, because they knew He was the Christ."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Preaches in Judea"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 1:35–39)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"At daybreak, Jesus went out to a solitary place, and the crowds were looking for Him. They came to Him and tried to keep Him from leaving.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"But Jesus told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I must preach the good news of the kingdom of God to the other towns as well, because that is why I was sent.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"And He continued to preach in the synagogues of Judea.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Galilee"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Mark 1:39"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The First Disciples"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 4:18–22; Mark 1:16–20; John 1:35–42)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"On one occasion, while Jesus was standing by the Lake of Gennesaret",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, the Sea of Galilee"]}],"caller":"+"},"with the crowd pressing in on Him to hear the word of God,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"He saw two boats at the edge of the lake. The fishermen had left them and were washing their nets.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Jesus got into the boat belonging to Simon and asked him to put out a little from shore. And sitting down, He taught the people from the boat."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"When Jesus had finished speaking, He said to Simon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Put out into deep water and let down your nets for a catch.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“Master,” Simon replied, “we have worked hard all night without catching anything. But because You say so, I will let down the nets.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"When they had done so, they caught such a large number of fish that their nets began to tear.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So they signaled to their partners in the other boat to come and help them, and they came and filled both boats so full that they began to sink."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"When Simon Peter saw this, he fell at Jesus’ knees. “Go away from me, Lord,” he said, “for I am a sinful man.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"For he and his companions were astonished at the catch of fish they had taken,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"and so were his partners James and John, the sons of Zebedee."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do not be afraid,” Jesus said to Simon."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“From now on you will catch men.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And when they had brought their boats ashore, they left everything and followed Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Leper’s Prayer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Leviticus 14:1–32; Matthew 8:1–4; Mark 1:40–45)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"While Jesus was in one of the towns, a man came along who was covered with leprosy.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Leprosy was a term used for various skin diseases. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"When he saw Jesus, he fell facedown and begged Him, “Lord, if You are willing, You can make me clean.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Jesus reached out His hand and touched the man."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I am willing,” He said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Be clean!” And immediately the leprosy left him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"“Do not tell anyone,” Jesus instructed him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“But go, show yourself to the priest and present the offering Moses prescribed for your cleansing, as a testimony to them.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["5:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 14:1–32"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But the news about Jesus spread all the more, and great crowds came to hear Him and to be healed of their sicknesses.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Yet He frequently withdrew to the wilderness to pray."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals a Paralytic"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:1–8; Mark 2:1–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"One day Jesus was teaching, and the Pharisees and teachers of the law were sitting there. People had come from Jerusalem and from every village of Galilee and Judea, and the power of the Lord was present for Him to heal the sick."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Just then some men came carrying a paralyzed man on a mat. They tried to bring him inside to set him before Jesus,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"but they could not find a way through the crowd. So they went up on the roof and lowered him on his mat through the tiles into the middle of the crowd, right in front of Jesus."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"When Jesus saw their faith, He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Friend, your sins are forgiven.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"But the scribes and Pharisees began thinking to themselves, “Who is this man who speaks blasphemy? Who can forgive sins but God alone?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Knowing what they were thinking, Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Why are you thinking these things in your hearts?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Which is easier: to say, ‘Your sins are forgiven,’or to say, ‘Get up and walk? ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But so that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on the earth to forgive sins…” He said to the paralytic,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I tell you, get up, pick up your mat, and go home.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"And immediately the man stood up before them, took what he had been lying on, and went home glorifying God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Everyone was taken with amazement and glorified God. They were filled with awe and said, “We have seen remarkable things today.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Calls Levi"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:9–13; Mark 2:13–17)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"After this, Jesus went out and saw a tax collector named Levi sitting at the tax booth."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Follow Me,” He told him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"and Levi got up, left everything, and followed Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Then Levi hosted a great banquet for Jesus at his house. A large crowd of tax collectors was there, along with others who were eating with them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But the Pharisees and their scribes complained to Jesus’ disciples, “Why do you eat and drink with tax collectors and sinners?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It is not the healthy who need a doctor, but the sick.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"I have not come to call the righteous, but sinners, to repentance.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Questions about Fasting"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:14–15; Mark 2:18–20)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Then they said to Him, “John’s disciples and those of the Pharisees frequently fast and pray, but Yours keep on eating and drinking.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Can you make the guests of the bridegroom fast while He is with them?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But the time will come when the bridegroom will be taken from them; then they will fast.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Patches and the Wineskins"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:16–17; Mark 2:21–22)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"He also told them a parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“No one tears a piece of cloth from a new garment and sews it on an old one. If he does, he will tear the new garment as well, and the patch from the new will not match the old."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"And no one pours new wine into old wineskins. If he does, the new wine will burst the skins, the wine will spill, and the wineskins will be ruined.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Instead, new wine is poured into new wineskins.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"And no one after drinking old wine wants new, for he says, ‘The old is better..”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Lord of the Sabbath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(1 Samuel 21:1–7; Matthew 12:1–8; Mark 2:23–28)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"One Sabbath",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["On the second Sabbath after the first"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Jesus was passing through the grainfields, and His disciples began to pick the heads of grain, rub them in their hands, and eat them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"But some of the Pharisees asked, “Why are you doing what is unlawful on the Sabbath?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Have you not read what David did when he and his companions were hungry?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"He entered the house of God, took the consecrated bread",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["the Bread of the Presence"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and gave it to his companions, and ate what is lawful only for the priests to eat.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then Jesus declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The Son of Man is Lord of the Sabbath.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals on the Sabbath"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 12:9–14; Mark 3:1–6)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"On another Sabbath Jesus entered the synagogue and was teaching, and a man was there whose right hand was withered.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Looking for a reason to accuse Jesus, the scribes and Pharisees were watching Him closely to see if He would heal on the Sabbath."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But Jesus knew their thoughts and said to the man with the withered hand,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Get up and stand among us.” So he got up and stood there."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I ask you, which is lawful on the Sabbath: to do good or to do evil, to save life or to destroy it?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"And after looking around at all of them, He said to the man,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Stretch out your hand.” He did so, and it was restored."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But the scribes and Pharisees were filled with rage and began to discuss with one another what they might do to Jesus."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Twelve Apostles"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 10:1–4; Mark 3:13–19)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"In those days Jesus went out to the mountain to pray, and He spent the night in prayer to God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When daylight came, He called His disciples to Him and chose twelve of them, whom He also designated as apostles:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Simon, whom He named Peter, and his brother Andrew; James and John; Philip and Bartholomew;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Matthew and Thomas; James son of Alphaeus and Simon called the Zealot;",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Judas son of James, and Judas Iscariot, who became a traitor."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals the Multitudes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 4:23–25; Mark 3:7–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Then Jesus came down with them and stood on a level place. A large crowd of His disciples was there, along with a great number of people from all over Judea, Jerusalem, and the seacoast of Tyre and Sidon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"They had come to hear Him and to be healed of their diseases, and those troubled by unclean spirits were healed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"The entire crowd was trying to touch Him, because power was coming from Him and healing them all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Beatitudes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Psalm 1:1–6; Matthew 5:3–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Looking up at His disciples, Jesus said:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Blessed are you who are poor,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for yours is the kingdom of God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Blessed are you who hunger now,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you will be filled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Blessed are you who weep now,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you will laugh."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Blessed are you when people hate you, and when they exclude you and insult you and reject your name as evil because of the Son of Man.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Rejoice in that day and leap for joy, because great is your reward in heaven. For their fathers treated the prophets in the same way."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Woes to the Satisfied"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Amos 6:1–7)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"But woe to you who are rich,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you have already received your comfort."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Woe to you who are well fed now,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you will hunger."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Woe to you who laugh now,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for you will mourn and weep."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Woe to you when all men speak well of you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for their fathers treated the false prophets in the same way."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Love Your Enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 5:38–48)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But to those of you who will listen, I say: Love your enemies, do good to those who hate you,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"bless those who curse you, pray for those who mistreat you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"If someone strikes you on one cheek, turn to him the other also. And if someone takes your cloak, do not withhold your tunic as well.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Give to everyone who asks you, and if anyone takes what is yours, do not demand it back.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Do to others as you would have them do to you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"If you love those who love you, what credit is that to you? Even sinners love those who love them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"If you do good to those who do good to you, what credit is that to you? Even sinners do the same.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"And if you lend to those from whom you expect repayment, what credit is that to you? Even sinners lend to sinners, expecting to be repaid in full."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But love your enemies, do good to them, and lend to them, expecting nothing in return. Then your reward will be great, and you will be sons of the Most High; for He is kind to the ungrateful and wicked.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Be merciful, just as your Father is merciful."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judging Others"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 7:1–6; Romans 14:1–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Do not judge, and you will not be judged. Do not condemn, and you will not be condemned. Forgive, and you will be forgiven.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Give, and it will be given to you. A good measure, pressed down, shaken together, and running over will be poured into your lap. For with the measure you use, it will be measured back to you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Jesus also told them a parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Can a blind man lead a blind man? Will they not both fall into a pit?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"A disciple is not above his teacher, but everyone who is fully trained will be like his teacher."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Why do you look at the speck in your brother’s eye but fail to notice the beam in your own eye?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"How can you say, ‘Brother,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:42"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["How can you say to your brother, ‘Brother"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"let me take the speck out of your eye,’while you yourself fail to see the beam in your own eye? You hypocrite! First take the beam out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to remove the speck from your brother’s eye."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Tree and Its Fruit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 7:15–23; Matthew 12:33–37)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"No good tree bears bad fruit, nor does a bad tree bear good fruit.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"For each tree is known by its own fruit. Indeed, figs are not gathered from thornbushes, nor grapes from brambles.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"The good man brings good things out of the good treasure of his heart, and the evil man brings evil things out of the evil treasure of his heart. For out of the overflow of the heart the mouth speaks."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The House on the Rock"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 7:24–27)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Why do you call Me ‘Lord, Lord,’but do not do what I say?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"I will show you what he is like who comes to Me and hears My words and acts on them:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"He is like a man building a house, who dug down deep and laid his foundation on the rock. When the flood came, the torrent crashed against that house but could not shake it, because it was well built.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["6:48"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["because its foundation was on the rock"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 7:25"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"But the one who hears My words and does not act on them is like a man who built his house on ground without a foundation. The torrent crashed against that house, and immediately it fell—and great was its destruction!”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Faith of the Centurion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 8:5–13; John 4:43–54)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"When Jesus had concluded His discourse in the hearing of the people, He went to Capernaum.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"There a highly valued servant of a centurion was sick and about to die.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"When the centurion heard about Jesus, he sent some Jewish elders to ask Him to come and heal his servant.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"They came to Jesus and pleaded with Him earnestly, “This man is worthy to have You grant this,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"for he loves our nation and has built our synagogue.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So Jesus went with them. But when He was not far from the house, the centurion sent friends with the message: “Lord, do not trouble Yourself, for I am not worthy to have You come under my roof.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"That is why I did not consider myself worthy to come to You. But just say the word, and my servant will be healed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"For I myself am a man under authority, with soldiers under me. I tell one to go, and he goes, and another to come, and he comes. I tell my servant to do something, and he does it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"When Jesus heard this, He marveled at the centurion. Turning to the crowd following Him, He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I tell you, not even in Israel have I found such great faith.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"And when the messengers returned to the house, they found the servant in good health."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Raises a Widow’s Son"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Soon afterward, Jesus went to a town called Nain. His disciples went with Him, accompanied by a large crowd.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"As He approached the town gate, He saw a dead man being carried out, the only son of his mother, and she was a widow. And a large crowd from the town was with her."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"When the Lord saw her, He had compassion on her and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do not weep.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"Then He went up and touched the coffin,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["bier"]},", probably a wooden plank or open coffin"]}],"caller":"+"},"and those carrying it stood still."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Young man,” He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I tell you, get up!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And the dead man sat up and began to speak! Then Jesus gave him back to his mother."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"A sense of awe swept over all of them, and they glorified God. “A great prophet has appeared among us!” they said. “God has visited His people!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And the news about Jesus spread throughout Judea and all the surrounding region."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["John’s Inquiry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 11:1–6)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then John’s disciples informed him about all these things.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"So John called two of his disciples and sent them to ask the Lord, “Are You the One who was to come, or should we look for someone else?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"When the men came to Jesus, they said, “John the Baptist sent us to ask, ‘Are You the One who was to come, or should we look for someone else?.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"At that very hour Jesus healed many people of their diseases, afflictions, and evil spirits, and He gave sight to many who were blind.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"So He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go back and report to John what you have seen and heard: The blind receive sight, the lame walk, the lepers",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["leper"]},"was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, and the good news is preached to the poor.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Blessed is the one who does not fall away on account of Me.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["who is not offended by Me"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Testifies about John"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Malachi 3:1–5; Matthew 11:7–19)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"After John’s messengers had left, Jesus began to speak to the crowds about John:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“What did you go out into the wilderness to see? A reed swaying in the wind?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Otherwise, what did you go out to see? A man dressed in fine clothes? Look, those who wear elegant clothing and live in luxury are found in palaces."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"What then did you go out to see? A prophet? Yes, I tell you, and more than a prophet.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"This is the one about whom it is written:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Behold, I will send My messenger ahead of You,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["who will prepare Your way before You.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Malachi 3:1"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"I tell you, among those born of women there is no one greater than John, yet even the least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"All the people who heard this, even the tax collectors, acknowledged God’s justice. For they had received the baptism of John.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But the Pharisees and experts in the law rejected God’s purpose for themselves, because they had not been baptized by John."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"“To what, then, can I compare the men of this generation? What are they like?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"They are like children sitting in the marketplace and calling out to one another:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘We played the flute for you,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and you did not dance;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["we sang a dirge,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and you did not weep. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"For John the Baptist came neither eating bread nor drinking wine, and you say, ‘He has a demon! ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"The Son of Man came eating and drinking, and you say, ‘Look at this glutton and drunkard, a friend of tax collectors and sinners! ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But wisdom is vindicated by all her children.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Sinful Woman Anoints Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:6–13; Mark 14:3–9; John 12:1–8)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Then one of the Pharisees invited Jesus to eat with him, and He entered the Pharisee’s house and reclined at the table.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"When a sinful woman from that town learned that Jesus was dining there, she brought an alabaster jar of perfume.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"As she stood behind Him at His feet weeping, she began to wet His feet with her tears and wipe them with her hair. Then she kissed His feet and anointed them with the perfume."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"When the Pharisee who had invited Jesus saw this, he said to himself, “If this man were a prophet, He would know who this is and what kind of woman is touching Him—for she is a sinner!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"But Jesus answered him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Simon, I have something to tell you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Tell me, Teacher,” he said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"“Two men were debtors to a certain moneylender. One owed him five hundred denarii,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["7:41"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 20:2"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"and the other fifty.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"When they were unable to repay him, he forgave both of them. Which one, then, will love him more?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"“I suppose the one who was forgiven more,” Simon replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You have judged correctly,” Jesus said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"And turning toward the woman, He said to Simon,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do you see this woman? When I entered your house, you did not give Me water for My feet, but she wet My feet with her tears and wiped them with her hair.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"You did not greet Me with a kiss, but she has not stopped kissing My feet since I arrived.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"You did not anoint My head with oil, but she has anointed My feet with perfume.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Therefore I tell you, her many sins have been forgiven, for she has loved much. But he who has been forgiven little loves little.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"Then Jesus said to her,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Your sins are forgiven.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"But those at the table began to say to themselves, “Who is this who even forgives sins?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"And Jesus told the woman,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Your faith has saved you; go in peace.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Women Minister to Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Soon afterward, Jesus traveled from one town and village to another, preaching and proclaiming the good news of the kingdom of God. The Twelve were with Him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"as well as some women who had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities: Mary called Magdalene, from whom seven demons had gone out,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Joanna the wife of Herod’s household manager Chuza, Susanna, and many others. These women were ministering to them",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to Him"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"out of their own means."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Sower"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 13:1–23; Mark 4:1–20)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"While a large crowd was gathering and people were coming to Jesus from town after town, He told them this parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"“A farmer went out to sow his seed. And as he was sowing, some seed fell along the path, where it was trampled, and the birds of the air devoured it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Some fell on rocky ground, and when it came up, the seedlings withered because they had no moisture."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Other seed fell among thorns, which grew up with it and choked the seedlings."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Still other seed fell on good soil, where it sprang up and produced a crop—a hundredfold.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["As Jesus said this, He called out,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“He who has ears to hear, let him hear.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then His disciples asked Him what this parable meant."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The knowledge of the mysteries of the kingdom of God has been given to you, but to others I speak in parables, so that,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘though seeing, they may not see;"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["though hearing, they may not understand.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:10"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 6:9"]},"(See also LXX)"]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Now this is the meaning of the parable: The seed is the word of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The seeds",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the ones"]},"; also in verses 13, 14, and 15"]}],"caller":"+"},"along the path are those who hear, but the devil comes and takes away the word from their hearts, so that they may not believe and be saved."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"The seeds on rocky ground are those who hear the word and receive it with joy, but they have no root. They believe for a season, but in the time of testing, they fall away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The seeds that fell among the thorns are those who hear, but as they go on their way, they are choked by the worries, riches, and pleasures of this life, and their fruit does not mature."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"But the seeds on good soil are those with a noble and good heart, who hear the word, cling to it, and by persevering produce a crop."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Lesson of the Lamp"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 4:21–25)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"No one lights a lamp and covers it with a jar or puts it under a bed. Instead, he sets it on a stand, so those who enter can see the light.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"For there is nothing hidden that will not be disclosed, and nothing concealed that will not be made known and brought to light."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Pay attention, therefore, to how you listen. Whoever has will be given more, but whoever does not have, even what he thinks he has will be taken away from him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus’ Mother and Brothers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 12:46–50; Mark 3:31–35)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Then Jesus’ mother and brothers came to see Him, but they were unable to reach Him because of the crowd.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"He was told, “Your mother and brothers are standing outside, wanting to see You.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"But He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“My mother and brothers are those who hear the word of God and carry it out.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Calms the Storm"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Psalm 107:1–43; Matthew 8:23–27; Mark 4:35–41)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"One day Jesus said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Let us cross to the other side of the lake.” So He got into a boat with them and set out."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"As they sailed, He fell asleep, and a windstorm came down on the lake, so that the boat was being swamped, and they were in great danger.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"The disciples went and woke Him, saying, “Master, Master, we are perishing!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Jesus got up and rebuked the wind and the raging waters, and they subsided, and all was calm."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"“Where is your faith?” He asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Frightened and amazed, they asked one another, “Who is this? He commands even the winds and the water, and they obey Him!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Demons and the Pigs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 8:28–34; Mark 5:1–20)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Then they sailed to the region of the Gerasenes,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:26"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Gadarenes"]},"; Tischendorf ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Gergesenes"]},"; also in verse 37"]}],"caller":"+"},"across the lake from Galilee.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"When Jesus stepped ashore, He was met by a demon-possessed man from the town. For a long time this man had not worn clothing or lived in a house, but he stayed in the tombs."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"When the man saw Jesus, he cried out and fell down before Him, shouting in a loud voice, “What do You want with me, Jesus, Son of the Most High God? I beg You not to torture me!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"For Jesus had commanded the unclean spirit to come out of the man. Many times it had seized him, and though he was bound with chains and shackles, he had broken the chains and been driven by the demon into solitary places."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"“What is your name?” Jesus asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Legion,” he replied, because many demons had gone into him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"And the demons kept begging Jesus not to order them to go into the Abyss."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"There on the hillside a large herd of pigs was feeding. So the demons begged Jesus to let them enter the pigs, and He gave them permission."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Then the demons came out of the man and went into the pigs, and the herd rushed down the steep bank into the lake and was drowned."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"When those tending the pigs saw what had happened, they ran off and reported this in the town and countryside.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"So the people went out to see what had happened. They came to Jesus and found the man whom the demons had left, sitting at Jesus’ feet, clothed and in his right mind; and they were afraid.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Meanwhile, those who had seen it reported how the demon-possessed man had been healed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Then all the people of the region of the Gerasenes asked Jesus to depart from them, because great fear had taken hold of them. So He got into the boat and started back."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"The man whom the demons had left begged to go with Jesus. But He sent him away, saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"“Return home and describe how much God has done for you.” So the man went away and proclaimed all over the town how much Jesus had done for him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Healing Touch of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:18–26; Mark 5:21–43)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"When Jesus returned, the crowd welcomed Him, for they had all been waiting for Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Just then a synagogue leader named Jairus came and fell at Jesus’ feet. He begged Him to come to his house,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"because his only daughter, who was about twelve, was dying."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["As Jesus went with him, the crowds pressed around Him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"including a woman who had suffered from bleeding for twelve years. She had spent all her money on physicians,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:43"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and WH do not include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["She had spent all her money on physicians"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"but no one was able to heal her.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"She came up behind Jesus and touched the fringe of His cloak, and immediately her bleeding stopped."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"“Who touched Me?” Jesus asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But they all denied it. “Master,” said Peter,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["8:45"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["and those who were with him"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"“the people are crowding and pressing against You.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"But Jesus declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Someone touched Me, for I know that power has gone out from Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Then the woman, seeing that she could not escape notice, came trembling and fell down before Him. In the presence of all the people, she explained why she had touched Him and how she had immediately been healed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"“Daughter,” said Jesus,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“your faith has healed you. Go in peace.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"While He was still speaking, someone arrived from the house of the synagogue leader. “Your daughter is dead,” he told Jairus. “Do not bother the Teacher anymore.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"But Jesus overheard them and said to Jairus,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do not be afraid; just believe, and she will be healed.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"When He entered the house, He did not allow anyone to go in with Him except Peter, John, James, and the child’s father and mother.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"Meanwhile, everyone was weeping and mourning for her. But Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Stop weeping; she is not dead but asleep.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"And they laughed at Him, knowing that she was dead."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"But Jesus took her by the hand and called out,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Child, get up!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"Her spirit returned, and at once she got up. And He directed that she be given something to eat.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"Her parents were astounded, but Jesus ordered them not to tell anyone what had happened."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Ministry of the Twelve"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 10:5–15; Mark 6:7–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then Jesus called the Twelve",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["His twelve disciples"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"together and gave them power and authority over all demons, and power to cure diseases.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And He sent them out to proclaim the kingdom of God and to heal the sick."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“Take nothing for the journey,” He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“no staff, no bag, no bread, no money,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:3"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["silver coins"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"no second tunic.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Whatever house you enter, stay there until you leave that area.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"If anyone does not welcome you, shake the dust off your feet when you leave that town, as a testimony against them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So they set out and went from village to village, preaching the gospel and healing people everywhere."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Herod Tries to See Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 14:1–12; Mark 6:14–29)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"When Herod the tetrarch heard about all that was happening, he was perplexed. For some were saying that John had risen from the dead,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"others that Elijah had appeared, and still others that a prophet of old had arisen."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“I beheaded John,” Herod said, “but who is this man I hear such things about?” And he kept trying to see Jesus."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Feeding of the Five Thousand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 14:13–21; Mark 6:30–44; John 6:1–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then the apostles returned and reported to Jesus all that they had done. Taking them away privately, He withdrew to a town called Bethsaida.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But the crowds found out and followed Him. He welcomed them and spoke to them about the kingdom of God, and He healed those who needed healing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"As the day neared its end, the Twelve came to Jesus and said, “Dismiss the crowd so they can go to the surrounding villages and countryside for lodging and provisions. For we are in a desolate place here.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But Jesus told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You give them something to eat.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“We have only five loaves of bread and two fish,” they answered, “unless we go and buy food for all these people.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"(- There were about five thousand men.)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He told His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Have them sit down in groups of about fifty each.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"They did so, and everyone was seated."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Taking the five loaves and the two fish and looking up to heaven, Jesus spoke a blessing and broke them. Then He gave them to the disciples to set before the people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"They all ate and were satisfied, and the disciples picked up twelve basketfuls of broken pieces that were left over."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Peter’s Confession of Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 16:13–20; Mark 8:27–30; John 6:67–71)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"One day as Jesus was praying in private and the disciples were with Him, He questioned them:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Who do the crowds say I am?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"They replied, “Some say John the Baptist; others say Elijah; and still others, that a prophet of old has arisen.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"“But what about you?” Jesus asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Who do you say I am?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Peter answered, “The Christ of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Christ’s Passion Foretold"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 16:21–23; Mark 8:31–33)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Jesus strictly warned them not to tell this to anyone."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"“The Son of Man must suffer many things,” He said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“He must be rejected by the elders, chief priests, and scribes, and He must be killed and on the third day be raised to life.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Take Up Your Cross"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 16:24–28; Mark 8:34–38)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Then Jesus said to all of them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“If anyone wants to come after Me, he must deny himself and take up his cross daily and follow Me.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For whoever wants to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life for My sake will save it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"What does it profit a man to gain the whole world, yet lose or forfeit his very self?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"If anyone is ashamed of Me and My words, the Son of Man will be ashamed of him when He comes in His glory and in the glory of the Father and of the holy angels.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But I tell you truly, some who are standing here will not taste death before they see the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Transfiguration"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 17:1–13; Mark 9:1–13; 2 Peter 1:16–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"About eight days after Jesus had said these things, He took with Him Peter, John, and James, and went up on a mountain to pray.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And as He was praying, the appearance of His face changed, and His clothes became radiantly white.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Suddenly two men, Moses and Elijah, began talking with Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"They appeared in glory and spoke about His departure, which He was about to accomplish at Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Meanwhile Peter and his companions were overcome by sleep, but when they awoke, they saw Jesus’ glory and the two men standing with Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"As Moses and Elijah were leaving, Peter said to Jesus, “Master, it is good for us to be here. Let us put up three shelters",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["three tabernacles"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"—one for You, one for Moses, and one for Elijah.” (He did not know what he was saying.)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"While Peter was speaking, a cloud appeared and enveloped them, and they were afraid as they entered the cloud.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"And a voice came from the cloud, saying, “This is My Son, whom I have chosen.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["This is My beloved Son"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 17:5"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"Listen to Him!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"After the voice had spoken, only Jesus was present with them. The disciples kept this to themselves, and in those days they did not tell anyone what they had seen."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Boy with an Evil Spirit"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 17:14–18; Mark 9:14–29)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"The next day, when they came down from the mountain, Jesus was met by a large crowd.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Suddenly a man in the crowd cried out, “Teacher, I beg You to look at my son, for he is my only child.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"A spirit keeps seizing him, and he screams abruptly. It throws him into convulsions so that he foams at the mouth. It keeps mauling him and rarely departs from him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"I begged Your disciples to drive it out, but they were unable.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"“O unbelieving and perverse generation!” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“How long must I remain with you and put up with you? Bring your son here.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Even while the boy was approaching, the demon slammed him to the ground in a convulsion. But Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, healed the boy, and gave him back to his father."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Second Prediction of the Passion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 17:22–23; Mark 9:30–32)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"And they were all astonished at the greatness of God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["While everyone was marveling at all that Jesus was doing, He said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"“Let these words sink into your ears: The Son of Man is about to be delivered into the hands of men.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"But they did not understand this statement. It was veiled from them so that they could not comprehend it, and they were afraid to ask Him about it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Greatest in the Kingdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 18:1–5; Mark 9:33–41)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Then an argument started among the disciples as to which of them would be the greatest.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"But Jesus, knowing the thoughts of their hearts, had a little child stand beside Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"And He said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Whoever welcomes this little child in My name welcomes Me, and whoever welcomes Me welcomes the One who sent Me. For whoever is the least among all of you, he is the greatest.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"“Master,” said John, “we saw someone driving out demons in Your name, and we tried to stop him, because he does not accompany us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"“Do not stop him,” Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“for whoever is not against you is for you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Samaritans Reject Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"As the day of His ascension approached, Jesus resolutely set out for Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"He sent messengers on ahead, who went into a village of the Samaritans to make arrangements for Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"But the people there refused to welcome Him, because He was heading for Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"When the disciples James and John saw this, they asked, “Lord, do You want us to call down fire from heaven",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:54"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["from heaven, just as Elijah did"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["2 Kings 1:10–12"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"to consume them?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"But Jesus turned and rebuked them.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["9:55"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["and He said, “You do not know what kind of spirit you are of. 56For the Son of Man did not come to destroy the lives of men, but to save them.”"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"And He and His disciples went on to another village."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Cost of Discipleship"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 8:18–22; Luke 14:25–33; John 6:59–66)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"As they were walking along the road, someone said to Jesus, “I will follow You wherever You go.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Foxes have dens and birds of the air have nests, but the Son of Man has no place to lay His head.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"Then He said to another man,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Follow Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["The man replied, “Lord, first let me go and bury my father.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"But Jesus told him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Let the dead bury their own dead. You, however, go and proclaim the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"Still another said, “I will follow You, Lord; but first let me bid farewell to my family.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"Then Jesus declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“No one who puts his hand to the plow and then looks back is fit for the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Sends the Seventy-Two"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 9:35–38)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"After this, the Lord appointed seventy-two",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE, BYZ, and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["seventy"]},"; also in verse 17"]}],"caller":"+"},"others and sent them two by two ahead of Him to every town and place He was about to visit.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The harvest is plentiful, but the workers are few. Ask the Lord of the harvest, therefore, to send out workers into His harvest."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Go! I am sending you out like lambs among wolves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Carry no purse or bag or sandals. Do not greet anyone along the road."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Whatever house you enter, begin by saying, ‘Peace to this house. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"If a man of peace is there, your peace will rest on him; if not, it will return to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Stay at the same house, eating and drinking whatever you are offered. For the worker is worthy of his wages.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 19:13"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 24:14–15"]},"; cited in",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["1 Timothy 5:18"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"Do not move around from house to house."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"If you enter a town and they welcome you, eat whatever is set before you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Heal the sick who are there and tell them, ‘The kingdom of God is near you. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But if you enter a town and they do not welcome you, go into the streets and declare,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"‘Even the dust of your town that clings to our feet, we wipe off as a testimony against you. Yet be sure of this: The kingdom of God is near. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I tell you, it will be more bearable on that day for Sodom than for that town."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Woe to the Unrepentant"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 11:20–24)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Woe to you, Chorazin! Woe to you, Bethsaida! For if the miracles that were performed in you had been performed in Tyre and Sidon, they would have repented long ago, sitting in sackcloth and ashes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But it will be more bearable for Tyre and Sidon at the judgment than for you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And you, Capernaum, will you be lifted up to heaven? No, you will be brought down to Hades!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Whoever listens to you listens to Me; whoever rejects you rejects Me; and whoever rejects Me rejects the One who sent Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Joyful Return"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"The seventy-two returned with joy and said, “Lord, even the demons submit to us in Your name.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"So He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I saw Satan fall like lightning from heaven.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Behold, I have given you authority to tread on snakes and scorpions, and over all the power of the enemy. Nothing will harm you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Nevertheless, do not rejoice that the spirits submit to you, but rejoice that your names are written in heaven.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus’ Prayer of Thanksgiving"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 11:25–30)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"At that time Jesus rejoiced in the Holy Spirit and declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I praise You, Father, Lord of heaven and earth, because You have hidden these things from the wise and learned, and revealed them to little children. Yes, Father, for this was well-pleasing in Your sight."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"All things have been entrusted to Me by My Father. No one knows who the Son is except the Father, and no one knows who the Father is except the Son and those to whom the Son chooses to reveal Him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Then Jesus turned to the disciples and said privately,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Blessed are the eyes that see what you see.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For I tell you that many prophets and kings desired to see what you see but did not see it, and to hear what you hear but did not hear it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Good Samaritan"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"One day an expert in the law stood up to test Him. “Teacher,” he asked, “what must I do to inherit eternal life?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"“What is written in the Law?” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“How do you read it?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"He answered, “‘Love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your strength and with all your mind’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 6:5"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and ‘Love your neighbor as yourself.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 19:18"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"“You have answered correctly,” Jesus said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do this and you will live.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"But wanting to justify himself, he asked Jesus, “And who is my neighbor?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Jesus took up this question and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“A man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho when he fell into the hands of robbers. They stripped him, beat him, and went away, leaving him half dead."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Now by chance a priest was going down the same road, but when he saw him, he passed by on the other side."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"So too, when a Levite came to that spot and saw him, he passed by on the other side."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"But a Samaritan on a journey came upon him, and when he saw him, he had compassion.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"He went to him and bandaged his wounds, pouring on oil and wine. Then he put him on his own animal, brought him to an inn, and took care of him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"The next day he took out two denarii",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 20:2"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"and gave them to the innkeeper. ‘Take care of him,’ he said, ‘and on my return I will repay you for any additional expense. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Which of these three do you think was a neighbor to the man who fell into the hands of robbers?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"“The one who showed him mercy,” replied the expert in the law."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Jesus told him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go and do likewise.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Martha and Mary"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"As they traveled along, Jesus entered a village where a woman named Martha welcomed Him into her home.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"She had a sister named Mary, who sat at the Lord’s feet listening to His message.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"But Martha was distracted by all the preparations to be made. She came to Jesus and said, “Lord, do You not care that my sister has left me to serve alone? Tell her to help me!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"“Martha, Martha,” the Lord replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“you are worried and upset about many things.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"But only one thing is necessary. Mary has chosen the good portion, and it will not be taken away from her.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Lord’s Prayer"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 6:5–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"One day in a place where Jesus had just finished praying, one of His disciples requested, “Lord, teach us to pray, just as John taught his disciples.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So Jesus told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“When you pray, say:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Father,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Our Father in heaven"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 6:9"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"hallowed be Your name."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Your kingdom come.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Your will be done, on earth as it is in heaven"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 6:10"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Give us each day our daily bread."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And forgive us our sins,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["for we also forgive everyone who sins against us."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And lead us not into temptation.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:4"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["but deliver us from the evil one"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 6:13"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"’”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Ask, Seek, Knock"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 7:7–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"Then Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Suppose one of you goes to his friend at midnight and says, ‘Friend, lend me three loaves of bread,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"because a friend of mine has come to me on a journey, and I have nothing to set before him. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And suppose the one inside answers, ‘Do not bother me. My door is already shut, and my children and I are in bed. I cannot get up to give you anything. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"I tell you, even though he will not get up to provide for him because of his friendship, yet because of the man’s persistence, he will get up and give him as much as he needs."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"So I tell you: Ask, and it will be given to you; seek, and you will find; knock, and the door will be opened to you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For everyone who asks receives; he who seeks finds; and to him who knocks, the door will be opened."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"What father among you, if his son asks for a fish,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["if his son asks for bread, will give him a stone, or for a fish"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 7:9–10"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"will give him a snake instead?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Or if he asks for an egg, will give him a scorpion?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So if you who are evil know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father in heaven give the Holy Spirit to those who ask Him!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A House Divided"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 12:22–30; Mark 3:20–27)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"One day Jesus was driving out a demon that was mute. And when the demon was gone, the man who had been mute spoke. The crowds were amazed,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"but some of them said, “It is by Beelzebul,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Beezeboul"]},"; Vulgate ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Beelzebub"]},"; also in verses 18 and 19"]}],"caller":"+"},"the prince of the demons, that He drives out demons.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"And others tested Him by demanding a sign from heaven."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Knowing their thoughts, Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Every kingdom divided against itself will be laid waste, and a house divided against a house will fall.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"If Satan is divided against himself, how can his kingdom stand? After all, you say that I drive out demons by Beelzebul.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And if I drive out demons by Beelzebul, by whom do your sons drive them out? So then, they will be your judges.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But if I drive out demons by the finger of God, then the kingdom of God has come upon you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"When a strong man, fully armed, guards his house, his possessions are secure.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But when someone stronger attacks and overpowers him, he takes away the armor in which the man trusted, and then he divides up his plunder."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"He who is not with Me is against Me, and he who does not gather with Me scatters."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["An Unclean Spirit Returns"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 12:43–45)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"When an unclean spirit comes out of a man, it passes through arid places seeking rest and does not find it. Then it says, ‘I will return to the house I left. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"On its return, it finds the house swept clean and put in order.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Then it goes and brings seven other spirits more wicked than itself, and they go in and dwell there. And the final plight of that man is worse than the first.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["True Blessedness"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"As Jesus was saying these things, a woman in the crowd raised her voice and said, “Blessed is the womb that bore You, and blessed are the breasts that nursed You!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Blessed rather are those who hear the word of God and obey it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Sign of Jonah"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Jonah 3:1–10; Matthew 12:38–42)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"As the crowds were increasing, Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“This is a wicked generation. It demands a sign, but none will be given it except the sign of Jonah.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For as Jonah was a sign to the Ninevites, so the Son of Man will be a sign to this generation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"The Queen of the South will rise at the judgment with the men of this generation and condemn them; for she came from the ends of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and now One greater than Solomon is here.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"The men of Nineveh will stand at the judgment with this generation and condemn it; for they repented at the preaching of Jonah, and now One greater than Jonah is here."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Lamp of the Body"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 6:22–24)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"No one lights a lamp and puts it in a cellar or under a basket. Instead, he sets it on a stand, so those who enter can see the light."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Your eye is the lamp of your body. When your eyes are good,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["When your eye is sound"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs 22:9"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"your whole body also is full of light. But when they are bad,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["when it is evil"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs 23:6"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs 28:22"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"your body is full of darkness.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Be careful, then, that the light within you is not darkness.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"So if your whole body is full of light, with no part of it in darkness, you will be radiant, as though a lamp were shining on you.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Woes to Pharisees and Experts in the Law"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 23:1–36)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"As Jesus was speaking, a Pharisee invited Him to dine with him; so He went in and reclined at the table.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"But the Pharisee was surprised to see that Jesus did not first wash before the meal."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Then the Lord said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Now you Pharisees clean the outside of the cup and dish, but inside you are full of greed and wickedness.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"You fools! Did not the One who made the outside make the inside as well?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"But give as alms the things that are within you, and behold, everything will be clean for you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Woe to you Pharisees! For you pay tithes of mint, rue, and every herb, but you disregard justice and the love of God. You should have practiced the latter without neglecting the former."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Woe to you Pharisees! For you love the chief seats in the synagogues and the greetings in the marketplaces.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Woe to you! For you are like unmarked graves, which men walk over without even noticing.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"One of the experts in the law told Him, “Teacher, when You say these things, You insult us as well.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"“Woe to you as well, experts in the law!” He replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“For you weigh men down with heavy burdens, but you yourselves will not lift a finger to lighten their load."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Woe to you! For you build tombs for the prophets, but it was your fathers who killed them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"So you are witnesses consenting to the deeds of your fathers: They killed the prophets, and you build their tombs.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"Because of this, the wisdom of God said, ‘I will send them prophets and apostles; some of them they will kill and others they will persecute. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"As a result, this generation will be charged with the blood of all the prophets that has been shed since the foundation of the world,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"from the blood of Abel to the blood of Zechariah, who was killed between the altar and the sanctuary.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["11:51"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the house"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Yes, I tell you, all of it will be charged to this generation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"Woe to you experts in the law! For you have taken away the key to knowledge. You yourselves have not entered, and you have hindered those who were entering.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"As Jesus went on from there, the scribes and Pharisees began to oppose Him bitterly and to ply Him with questions about many things,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"waiting to catch Him in something He might say."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Leaven of the Pharisees"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 16:5–12; Mark 8:14–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"In the meantime, a crowd of many thousands had gathered, so that they were trampling one another. Jesus began to speak first to His disciples:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Beware of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"There is nothing concealed that will not be disclosed, and nothing hidden that will not be made known.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"What you have spoken in the dark will be heard in the daylight, and what you have whispered in the inner rooms will be proclaimed from the housetops."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Fear God Alone"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 10:26–31)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"I tell you, My friends, do not be afraid of those who kill the body and after that can do no more.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But I will show you whom you should fear: Fear the One who, after you have been killed, has authority to throw you into hell.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Gehenna"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Yes, I tell you, fear Him!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Are not five sparrows sold for two pennies?",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["two assaria"]},"; an assarion was a Roman copper coin worth about 1/16 of a denarius."]}],"caller":"+"},"Yet not one of them is forgotten by God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And even the very hairs of your head are all numbered. So do not be afraid; you are worth more than many sparrows."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Confessing Christ"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 10:32–33)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"I tell you, everyone who confesses Me before men, the Son of Man will also confess him before the angels of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"But whoever denies Me before men will be denied before the angels of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"And everyone who speaks a word against the Son of Man will be forgiven, but whoever blasphemes against the Holy Spirit will not be forgiven."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"When you are brought before synagogues, rulers, and authorities, do not worry about how to defend yourselves or what to say.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"For at that time the Holy Spirit will teach you what you should say.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Rich Fool"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Someone in the crowd said to Him, “Teacher, tell my brother to divide the inheritance with me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Man, who appointed Me judge or executor between you?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And He said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Watch out! Guard yourselves against every form of greed, for one’s life does not consist in the abundance of his possessions.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then He told them a parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The ground of a certain rich man produced an abundance.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"So he thought to himself, ‘What shall I do, since I have nowhere to store my crops? ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then he said, ‘This is what I will do: I will tear down my barns and will build bigger ones, and there I will store up all my grain and my goods.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Then I will say to myself, “You have plenty of good things laid up for many years. Take it easy. Eat, drink, and be merry!” ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But God said to him, ‘You fool! This very night your life will be required of you. Then who will own what you have accumulated? ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"This is how it will be for anyone who stores up treasure for himself but is not rich toward God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Do Not Worry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 6:25–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then Jesus said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Therefore I tell you, do not worry about your life, what you will eat, or about your body, what you will wear.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"For life is more than food, and the body more than clothes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Consider the ravens: They do not sow or reap, they have no storehouse or barn; yet God feeds them. How much more valuable you are than the birds!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Who of you by worrying can add a single hour to his life?",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:25"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["a single cubit to his height"]},"; a cubit was approximately 18 inches or 45 centimeters."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So if you cannot do such a small thing, why do you worry about the rest?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Consider how the lilies grow: They do not labor or spin.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NE and Tischendorf ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Consider the lilies: They do not spin or weave."]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Yet I tell you, not even Solomon in all his glory was adorned like one of these.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"If that is how God clothes the grass of the field, which is here today and tomorrow is thrown into the furnace, how much more will He clothe you, O you of little faith!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And do not be concerned about what you will eat or drink. Do not worry about it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"For the Gentiles of the world strive after all these things, and your Father knows that you need them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"But seek His",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:31"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["God’s"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 6:33"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"kingdom, and these things will be added unto you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Treasures in Heaven"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 6:19–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Do not be afraid, little flock, for your Father is pleased to give you the kingdom.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Sell your possessions and give to the poor. Provide yourselves with purses that will not wear out, an inexhaustible treasure in heaven, where no thief approaches and no moth destroys.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"For where your treasure is, there your heart will be also."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Readiness at Any Hour"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:36–51; Mark 13:32–37)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Be dressed for service and keep your lamps burning.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"Then you will be like servants waiting for their master to return from the wedding banquet, so that when he comes and knocks, they can open the door for him at once.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Blessed are those servants whom the master finds on watch when he returns. Truly I tell you, he will dress himself to serve and will have them recline at the table, and he himself will come and wait on them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Even if he comes in the second or third watch of the night",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, between nine at night and three in the morning"]}],"caller":"+"},"and finds them alert, those servants will be blessed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"But understand this: If the homeowner had known at what hour the thief was coming,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:39"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["he would have stayed awake, and"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"he would not have let his house be broken into.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"You also must be ready, because the Son of Man will come at an hour you do not expect.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"“Lord,” said Peter, “are You addressing this parable to us, or to everyone else as well?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"And the Lord answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Who then is the faithful and wise manager, whom the master puts in charge of his servants to give them their portion at the proper time?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Blessed is that servant whose master finds him doing so when he returns.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Truly I tell you, he will put him in charge of all his possessions."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"But suppose that servant says in his heart, ‘My master will be a long time in coming,’and he begins to beat the menservants and maidservants, and to eat and drink and get drunk.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"The master of that servant will come on a day he does not expect and at an hour he does not anticipate. Then he will cut him to pieces and assign him a place with the unbelievers."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"That servant who knows his master’s will but does not get ready or follow his instructions will be beaten with many blows.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"But the one who unknowingly does things worthy of punishment will be beaten with few blows. From everyone who has been given much, much will be required; and from him who has been entrusted with much, even more will be demanded."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Not Peace but Division"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Micah 7:1–6; Matthew 10:34–39)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"I have come to ignite a fire on the earth, and how I wish it were already kindled!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"But I have a baptism to undergo, and how distressed I am until it is accomplished!"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"Do you think that I have come to bring peace to the earth? No, I tell you, but division.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"From now on, five in one household will be divided, three against two and two against three.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"They will be divided, father against son and son against father, mother against daughter and daughter against mother, mother-in-law against daughter-in-law and daughter-in-law against mother-in-law.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:53"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Micah 7:6"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Interpreting the Present Time"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 16:1–4; Mark 8:11–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"Then Jesus said to the crowds,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“As soon as you see a cloud rising in the west, you say, ‘A shower is coming,’and that is what happens.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"And when the south wind blows, you say, ‘It will be hot,’and it is.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"You hypocrites! You know how to interpret the appearance of the earth and sky. Why don’t you know how to interpret the present time?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Reconciling with an Adversary"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 5:21–26)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"And why don’t you judge for yourselves what is right?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"Make every effort to reconcile with your adversary while you are on your way to the magistrate. Otherwise, he may drag you off to the judge, and the judge may hand you over to the officer, and the officer may throw you into prison.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"I tell you, you will not get out until you have paid the very last penny.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["12:59"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["lepton"]},"; that is, a Jewish coin of bronze or copper worth about 1/128 of a denarius"]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["A Call to Repentance"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Joel 1:13–20; Amos 5:4–15; Zephaniah 2:1–3)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"At that time some of those present told Jesus about the Galileans whose blood Pilate had mixed with their sacrifices.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"To this He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do you think that these Galileans were worse sinners than all the other Galileans, because they suffered this way?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"No, I tell you. But unless you repent, you too will all perish.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Or those eighteen who were killed when the tower of Siloam collapsed on them: Do you think that they were more sinful than all the others living in Jerusalem?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"No, I tell you. But unless you repent, you too will all perish.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Barren Fig Tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 5:1–7)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Then Jesus told this parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“A man had a fig tree that was planted in his vineyard. He went to look for fruit on it but did not find any.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So he said to the keeper of the vineyard, ‘Look, for the past three years I have come to search for fruit on this fig tree and haven’t found any. Therefore cut it down!",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["SBL, NE, WH ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Cut it down!"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Why should it use up the soil? ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"‘Sir,’ the man replied, ‘leave it alone again this year, until I dig around it and fertilize it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"If it bears fruit next year, fine. But if not, you can cut it down..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals a Disabled Woman"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"One Sabbath Jesus was teaching in one of the synagogues,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and a woman there had been disabled by a spirit for eighteen years. She was hunched over and could not stand up straight.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"When Jesus saw her, He called her over and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Woman, you are set free from your disability.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then He placed His hands on her, and immediately she straightened up and began to glorify God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But the synagogue leader was indignant that Jesus had healed on the Sabbath. “There are six days for work,” he told the crowd. “So come and be healed on those days and not on the Sabbath.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"“You hypocrites!” the Lord replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Does not each of you on the Sabbath untie his ox or donkey from the stall and lead it to water?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Then should not this daughter of Abraham, whom Satan has kept bound for eighteen long years, be released from her bondage on the Sabbath day?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"When Jesus said this, all His adversaries were humiliated. And the whole crowd rejoiced at all the glorious things He was doing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Mustard Seed"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 13:31–32; Mark 4:30–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then Jesus asked,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“What is the kingdom of God like? To what can I compare it?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"It is like a mustard seed that a man tossed into his garden. It grew and became a tree, and the birds of the air nested in its branches.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Leaven"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 13:33)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Again He asked,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“To what can I compare the kingdom of God?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"It is like leaven that a woman took and mixed into three measures of flour, until all of it was leavened.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Narrow Door"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 7:13–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then Jesus traveled throughout the towns and villages, teaching as He made His way toward Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"“Lord,” someone asked Him, “will only a few people be saved?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“Make every effort to enter through the narrow door. For many, I tell you, will try to enter and will not be able.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"After the master of the house gets up and shuts the door, you will stand outside knocking and saying, ‘Lord, open the door for us. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But he will reply, ‘I do not know where you are from. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Then you will say, ‘We ate and drank with you, and you taught in our streets. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And he will answer, ‘I tell you, I do not know where you are from. Depart from me, all you evildoers. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"There will be weeping and gnashing of teeth when you see Abraham, Isaac, Jacob, and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, but you yourselves are thrown out.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"People will come from east and west and north and south, and will recline at the table in the kingdom of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"And indeed, some who are last will be first, and some who are first will be last.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Lament over Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 23:37–39)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"At that very hour, some Pharisees came to Jesus and told Him, “Leave this place and get away, because Herod wants to kill You.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"But Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go tell that fox, ‘Look, I will keep driving out demons and healing people today and tomorrow, and on the third day I will reach My goal. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Nevertheless, I must keep going today and tomorrow and the next day, for it is not admissible for a prophet to perish outside of Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"O Jerusalem, Jerusalem, who kills the prophets and stones those sent to her, how often I have longed to gather your children together as a hen gathers her chicks under her wings, but you were unwilling!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Look, your house is left to you desolate. And I tell you that you will not see Me again until you say, ‘Blessed is He who comes in the name of the Lord.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["13:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 118:26"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals a Man with Dropsy"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"One Sabbath, Jesus went to eat in the home of a leading Pharisee, and those in attendance were watching Him closely.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"Right there before Him was a man with dropsy.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So Jesus asked the experts in the law and the Pharisees,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath or not?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"But they remained silent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Jesus took hold of the man, healed him, and sent him on his way.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And He asked them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Which of you whose son",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:5"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["donkey"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"or ox falls into a pit on the Sabbath day will not immediately pull him out?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And they were unable to answer these questions."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Guests"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"When Jesus noticed how the guests chose the places of honor, He told them a parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"“When you are invited to a wedding banquet, do not sit in the place of honor, in case someone more distinguished than you has been invited.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then the host who invited both of you will come and tell you, ‘Give this man your seat. ’And in humiliation, you will have to take the last place."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"But when you are invited, go and sit in the last place, so that your host will come and tell you, ‘Friend, move up to a better place.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:10"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs 25:7"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"Then you will be honored in front of everyone at the table with you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, and the one who humbles himself will be exalted.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then Jesus said to the man who had invited Him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“When you host a dinner or a banquet, do not invite your friends or brothers or relatives or rich neighbors. Otherwise, they may invite you in return, and you will be repaid.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But when you host a banquet, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, and the blind,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and you will be blessed. Since they cannot repay you, you will be repaid at the resurrection of the righteous.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Banquet"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 22:1–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When one of those reclining with Him heard this, he said to Jesus, “Blessed is everyone who will eat at the feast",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["14:15"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["who will eat bread"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"in the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“A certain man prepared a great banquet and invited many guests.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"When it was time for the banquet, he sent his servant to tell those who had been invited, ‘Come, for everything is now ready. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But one after another they all began to make excuses. The first one said, ‘I have bought a field, and I need to go see it. Please excuse me. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Another said, ‘I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I am going to try them out. Please excuse me. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Still another said, ‘I have married a wife, so I cannot come. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"The servant returned and reported all this to his master. Then the owner of the house became angry and said to his servant, ‘Go out quickly into the streets and alleys of the city, and bring in the poor, the crippled, the blind, and the lame. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"‘Sir,’ the servant replied, ‘what you ordered has been done, and there is still room. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"So the master told his servant, ‘Go out to the highways and hedges and compel them to come in, so that my house will be full.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For I tell you, not one of those men who were invited will taste my banquet..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Cost of Discipleship"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 8:18–22; Luke 9:57–62; John 6:59–66)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Now large crowds were traveling with Jesus, and He turned and said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"“If anyone comes to Me and does not hate his father and mother and wife and children and brothers and sisters—yes, even his own life—he cannot be My disciple.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And whoever does not carry his cross and follow Me cannot be My disciple."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"Which of you, wishing to build a tower, does not first sit down and count the cost to see if he has the resources to complete it?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Otherwise, if he lays the foundation and is unable to finish the work, everyone who sees it will ridicule him,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"saying, ‘This man could not finish what he started to build. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Or what king on his way to war with another king will not first sit down and consider whether he can engage with ten thousand men the one coming against him with twenty thousand?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"And if he is unable, he will send a delegation while the other king is still far off, to ask for terms of peace."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"In the same way, any one of you who does not give up everything he has cannot be My disciple."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Good Salt"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 5:13–16; Mark 9:49–50)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Salt is good, but if the salt loses its savor, with what will it be seasoned?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"It is fit neither for the soil nor for the manure pile, and it is thrown out."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He who has ears to hear, let him hear.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Lost Sheep"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 18:10–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now all the tax collectors and sinners were gathering around to listen to Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So the Pharisees and scribes began to grumble: “This man welcomes sinners and eats with them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then Jesus told them this parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"“What man among you, if he has a hundred sheep and loses one of them, does not leave the ninety-nine in the pasture and go after the one that is lost, until he finds it?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And when he finds it, he joyfully puts it on his shoulders,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"comes home, and calls together his friends and neighbors to tell them, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have found my lost sheep! ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"I tell you that in the same way there will be more joy in heaven over one sinner who repents than over ninety-nine righteous ones who do not need to repent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Lost Coin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Or what woman who has ten silver coins",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:8"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["ten drachmas"]},", each worth about a day’s wages"]}],"caller":"+"},"and loses one of them does not light a lamp, sweep her house, and search carefully until she finds it?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And when she finds it, she calls together her friends and neighbors to say, ‘Rejoice with me, for I have found my lost coin. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"In the same way, I tell you, there is joy in the presence of God’s angels over one sinner who repents.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Prodigal Son"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Deuteronomy 21:18–21)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"Then Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“There was a man who had two sons.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"The younger son said to him, ‘Father, give me my share of the estate. ’So he divided his property between them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"After a few days, the younger son got everything together and journeyed to a distant country, where he squandered his wealth in wild living."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"After he had spent all he had, a severe famine swept through that country, and he began to be in need.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So he went and hired himself out to a citizen of that country, who sent him into his fields to feed the pigs.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"He longed to fill his belly with the pods the pigs were eating, but no one would give him a thing."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Finally he came to his senses and said, ‘How many of my father’s hired servants have plenty of food, but here I am, starving to death!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"I will get up and go back to my father and say to him, “Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"I am no longer worthy to be called your son. Make me like one of your hired servants.” ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So he got up and went to his father. But while he was still in the distance, his father saw him and was filled with compassion. He ran to his son, embraced him, and kissed him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"The son declared, ‘Father, I have sinned against heaven and against you. I am no longer worthy to be called your son.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["15:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["WH includes ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Make me like one of your hired servants"]},"; see verse 19."]}],"caller":"+"},"’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"But the father said to his servants, ‘Quick! Bring the best robe and put it on him. Put a ring on his finger and sandals on his feet.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Bring the fattened calf and kill it. Let us feast and celebrate.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For this son of mine was dead and is alive again! He was lost and is found! ’So they began to celebrate."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Meanwhile the older son was in the field, and as he approached the house, he heard music and dancing.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"So he called one of the servants and asked what was going on."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"‘Your brother has returned,’ he said, ‘and your father has killed the fattened calf, because he has him back safe and sound. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"The older son became angry and refused to go in. So his father came out and pleaded with him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"But he answered his father, ‘Look, all these years I have served you and never disobeyed a commandment of yours. Yet you never gave me even a young goat so I could celebrate with my friends.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"But when this son of yours returns from squandering your wealth with prostitutes, you kill the fattened calf for him! ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"‘Son, you are always with me,’ the father said, ‘and all that is mine is yours.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"But it was fitting to celebrate and be glad, because this brother of yours was dead and is alive again; he was lost and is found..”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Shrewd Manager"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Jesus also said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“There was a rich man whose manager was accused of wasting his possessions.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"So he called him in to ask, ‘What is this I hear about you? Turn in an account of your management, for you cannot be manager any longer. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"The manager said to himself, ‘What shall I do, now that my master is taking away my position? I am too weak to dig and too ashamed to beg.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"I know what I will do so that after my removal from management, people will welcome me into their homes. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"And he called in each one of his master’s debtors. ‘How much do you owe my master? ’he asked the first."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"‘A hundred measures of olive oil,’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:6"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["‘A hundred baths of oil’"]},"; that is, approximately 870 gallons or 3,300 liters"]}],"caller":"+"},"he answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["‘Take your bill,’ said the manager, ‘sit down quickly, and write fifty. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then he asked another, ‘And how much do you owe?’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["‘A hundred measures of wheat,’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:7"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["‘A hundred cors of wheat’"]},"; that is, approximately 1,000 bushels or 35,000 liters (probably about 30 tons or 27 metric tons of wheat)"]}],"caller":"+"},"he replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["‘Take your bill and write eighty,’he told him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"The master commended the dishonest manager because he had acted shrewdly. For the sons of this age are more shrewd in dealing with their own kind than are the sons of light.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"I tell you, use worldly wealth to make friends for yourselves so that when it is gone, they will welcome you into eternal dwellings."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Whoever is faithful with very little will also be faithful with much, and whoever is dishonest with very little will also be dishonest with much.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"So if you have not been faithful with worldly wealth, who will entrust you with true riches?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And if you have not been faithful with the belongings of another, who will give you belongings of your own?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"No servant can serve two masters. Either he will hate the one and love the other, or he will be devoted to the one and despise the other. You cannot serve both God and money.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Law and the Prophets"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"The Pharisees, who were lovers of money, heard all of this and were scoffing at Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So He said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You are the ones who justify yourselves before men, but God knows your hearts. For what is prized among men is detestable before God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The Law and the Prophets were proclaimed until John. Since that time, the gospel of the kingdom of God is being preached, and everyone is forcing his way into it.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["everyone is urged to enter into it"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But it is easier for heaven and earth to pass away than for a single stroke of a pen to drop out of the Law."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Anyone who divorces his wife and marries another woman commits adultery, and he who marries a divorced woman commits adultery."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Rich Man and Lazarus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(John 5:39–47)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Now there was a rich man dressed in purple and fine linen, who lived each day in joyous splendor.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"And a beggar named Lazarus lay at his gate, covered with sores",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"and longing to be fed with the crumbs that fell from the rich man’s table. Even the dogs came and licked his sores."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"One day the beggar died and was carried by the angels to Abraham’s side.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["16:22"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["into Abraham’s bosom"]},"; similarly in verse 23"]}],"caller":"+"},"And the rich man also died and was buried.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"In Hades, where he was in torment, he looked up and saw Abraham from afar, with Lazarus by his side."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"So he cried out, ‘Father Abraham, have mercy on me and send Lazarus to dip the tip of his finger in water and cool my tongue. For I am in agony in this fire. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But Abraham answered, ‘Child, remember that during your lifetime you received your good things, while Lazarus received bad things. But now he is comforted here, while you are in agony.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"And besides all this, a great chasm has been fixed between us and you, so that even those who wish cannot cross from here to you, nor can anyone cross from there to us. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"‘Then I beg you, father,’ he said, ‘send Lazarus to my father’s house,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"for I have five brothers. Let him warn them, so that they will not also end up in this place of torment. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"But Abraham replied, ‘They have Moses and the Prophets; let your brothers listen to them. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"‘No, father Abraham,’ he said, ‘but if someone is sent to them from the dead, they will repent. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then Abraham said to him, ‘If they do not listen to Moses and the Prophets, they will not be persuaded even if someone rises from the dead..”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Temptations and Trespasses"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 18:6–9; Mark 9:42–48)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Jesus said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It is inevitable that stumbling blocks will come, but woe to the one through whom they come!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"It would be better for him to have a millstone hung around his neck and to be thrown into the sea than to cause one of these little ones to stumble."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Watch yourselves. If your brother sins, rebuke him; and if he repents, forgive him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Even if he sins against you seven times in a day, and seven times returns to say, ‘I repent,’you must forgive him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Power of Faith"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 17:19–20)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"The apostles said to the Lord, “Increase our faith!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And the Lord answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“If you have faith the size of a mustard seed, you can say to this mulberry tree, ‘Be uprooted and planted in the sea,’and it will obey you."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Which of you whose servant comes in from plowing or shepherding in the field will say to him, ‘Come at once and sit down to eat’?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Instead, won’t he tell him, ‘Prepare my meal and dress yourself to serve me while I eat and drink, and afterward you may eat and drink’?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Does he thank the servant because he did what he was told?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"So you also, when you have done everything commanded of you, should say, ‘We are unworthy servants; we have only done our duty..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Ten Lepers"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(2 Kings 5:1–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"While Jesus was on His way to Jerusalem, He was passing between Samaria and Galilee.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"As He entered one of the villages, He was met by ten lepers.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:12"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["leper"]},"was one afflicted with a skin disease. See Leviticus 13."]}],"caller":"+"},"They stood at a distance",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"and raised their voices, shouting, “Jesus, Master, have mercy on us!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"When Jesus saw them, He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go, show yourselves to the priests.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:14"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Leviticus 14:1–32"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"And as they were on their way, they were cleansed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When one of them saw that he was healed, he came back, praising God in a loud voice.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"He fell facedown at Jesus’ feet in thanksgiving to Him—and he was a Samaritan."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"“Were not all ten cleansed?” Jesus asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Where then are the other nine?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Was no one found except this foreigner to return and give glory to God?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"Then Jesus said to him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Rise and go; your faith has made you well!",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:19"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["has saved you"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Coming of the Kingdom"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Genesis 19:24–29)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"When asked by the Pharisees when the kingdom of God would come, Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The kingdom of God will not come with observable signs.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Nor will people say, ‘Look, here it is,’or ‘There it is. ’For you see, the kingdom of God is in your midst.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:21"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["within you"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["within your grasp"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Then He said to the disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The time is coming when you will long to see one of the days of the Son of Man, but you will not see it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"People will tell you, ‘Look, there He is! ’or ‘Look, here He is! ’Do not go out or chase after them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"For just as the lightning flashes and lights up the sky from one end to the other, so will be the Son of Man in His day.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"But first He must suffer many things and be rejected by this generation."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Just as it was in the days of Noah, so also will it be in the days of the Son of Man:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"People were eating and drinking, marrying and being given in marriage, up to the day Noah entered the ark. Then the flood came and destroyed them all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"It was the same in the days of Lot: People were eating and drinking, buying and selling, planting and building.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"But on the day Lot left Sodom, fire and sulfur rained down from heaven and destroyed them all."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"It will be just like that on the day the Son of Man is revealed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"On that day, let no one on the housetop come down to retrieve his possessions. Likewise, let no one in the field return for anything he has left behind.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Remember Lot’s wife!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Whoever tries to save his life will lose it, but whoever loses his life will preserve it.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"I tell you, on that night two people will be in one bed: one will be taken and the other left.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Two women will be grinding grain together: one will be taken and the other left.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR includes ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["36Two men will be in the field. One will be taken and the other left"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 24:40"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"“Where, Lord?” they asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Wherever there is a carcass, there the vultures will gather.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Persistent Widow"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then Jesus told them a parable about their need to pray at all times and not lose heart:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“In a certain town there was a judge who neither feared God nor respected men.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"And there was a widow in that town who kept appealing to him, ‘Give me justice against my adversary. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For a while he refused, but later he said to himself, ‘Though I neither fear God nor respect men,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"yet because this widow keeps pestering me, I will give her justice. Otherwise, she will wear me out with her perpetual requests..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"And the Lord said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Listen to the words of the unjust judge.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Will not God bring about justice for His elect who cry out to Him day and night? Will He delay in helping them?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"I tell you, He will promptly carry out justice on their behalf. Nevertheless, when the Son of Man comes, will He find faith on earth?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Pharisee and the Tax Collector"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"To some who trusted in their own righteousness and viewed others with contempt, He also told this parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"“Two men went up to the temple to pray. One was a Pharisee and the other a tax collector.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"The Pharisee stood by himself and prayed,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:11"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["stood and prayed to himself"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"‘God, I thank You that I am not like other men—swindlers, evildoers, adulterers—or even like this tax collector.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"I fast twice a week and pay tithes of all that I acquire. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"But the tax collector stood at a distance, unwilling even to lift up his eyes to heaven. Instead, he beat his breast and said, ‘God, have mercy on me, a sinner! ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"I tell you, this man, rather than the Pharisee, went home justified. For everyone who exalts himself will be humbled, but the one who humbles himself will be exalted.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Blesses the Children"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 19:13–15; Mark 10:13–16)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Now people were even bringing their babies to Jesus for Him to place His hands on them. And when the disciples saw this, they rebuked those who brought them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But Jesus called the children to Him and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Let the little children come to Me, and do not hinder them! For the kingdom of God belongs to such as these.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"Truly I tell you, anyone who does not receive the kingdom of God like a little child will never enter it.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Rich Young Ruler"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 19:16–30; Mark 10:17–31)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Then a certain ruler asked Him, “Good Teacher, what must I do to inherit eternal life?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"“Why do you call Me good?” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“No one is good except God alone.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"You know the commandments: ‘Do not commit adultery, do not murder, do not steal, do not bear false witness, honor your father and mother.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 20:12–16"]},";",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 5:16–20"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“All these I have kept from my youth,” he said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"On hearing this, Jesus told him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You still lack one thing: Sell everything you own and give to the poor, and you will have treasure in heaven. Then come, follow Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But when the ruler heard this, he became very sad, because he was extremely wealthy."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Seeing the man’s sadness,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["Seeing that he had become sorrowful"]},"; SBL, NE, and WH ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Seeing him"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“How hard it is for the rich to enter the kingdom of God!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Indeed, it is easier for a camel to pass through the eye of a needle than for a rich man to enter the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Those who heard this asked, “Who then can be saved?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"But Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“What is impossible with man is possible with God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"“Look,” said Peter, “we have left all we had",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["18:28"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["left our own"]},"; BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["left all"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"to follow You.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"“Truly I tell you,” Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“no one who has left home or wife or brothers or parents or children for the sake of the kingdom of God",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"will fail to receive many times more in this age—and in the age to come, eternal life.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Third Prediction of the Passion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 20:17–19; Mark 10:32–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then Jesus took the Twelve aside and said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Look, we are going up to Jerusalem, and everything the prophets have written about the Son of Man will be fulfilled.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"He will be delivered over to the Gentiles and will be mocked and insulted and spit upon.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"They will flog Him and kill Him, and on the third day He will rise again.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"But the disciples did not understand any of these things. The meaning was hidden from them, and they did not comprehend what He was saying."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Heals a Blind Beggar"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 20:29–34; Mark 10:46–52)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"As Jesus drew near to Jericho, a blind man was sitting beside the road, begging.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"When he heard the crowd going by, he asked what was happening."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"“Jesus of Nazareth is passing by,” they told him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"So he called out, “Jesus, Son of David, have mercy on me!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Those who led the way admonished him to be silent, but he cried out all the louder, “Son of David, have mercy on me!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"Jesus stopped and directed that the man be brought to Him. When he had come near, Jesus asked him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"“What do you want Me to do for you?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Lord,” he said, “let me see again.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"“Receive your sight!” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Your faith has healed you.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Immediately he received his sight and followed Jesus, glorifying God. And all the people, when they saw it, gave praise to God."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus and Zacchaeus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Numbers 5:5–10)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then Jesus entered Jericho and was passing through.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And there was a man named Zacchaeus, a chief tax collector, who was very wealthy.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"He was trying to see who Jesus was, but could not see over the crowd because he was small in stature.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"So he ran on ahead and climbed a sycamore tree to see Him, since Jesus was about to pass that way."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"When Jesus came to that place, He looked up and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Zacchaeus, hurry down, for I must stay at your house today.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"So Zacchaeus hurried down and welcomed Him joyfully.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And all who saw this began to grumble, saying, “He has gone to be the guest of a sinful man!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"But Zacchaeus stood up and said to the Lord, “Look, Lord, half of my possessions I give to the poor, and if I have cheated anyone, I will repay it fourfold.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Jesus said to him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Today salvation has come to this house, because this man too is a son of Abraham.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"For the Son of Man came to seek and to save the lost.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Ten Minas"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 25:14–30)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"While the people were listening to this, Jesus proceeded to tell them a parable, because He was near Jerusalem and they thought the kingdom of God would appear imminently.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"So He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“A man of noble birth went to a distant country to lay claim to his kingship and then return.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Beforehand, he called ten of his servants and gave them ten minas.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, he gave each servant one mina. A mina was most likely a silver coin worth a hundred drachmas, that is, about a hundred days’ wages."]}],"caller":"+"},"‘Conduct business with this until I return,’ he said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But his subjects hated him and sent a delegation after him to say, ‘We do not want this man to rule over us. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"When he returned from procuring his kingship, he summoned the servants to whom he had given the money, to find out what each one had earned."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"The first servant came forward and said, ‘Master, your mina has produced ten more minas. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"His master replied, ‘Well done, good servant! Because you have been faithful in a very small matter, you shall have authority over ten cities. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"The second servant came and said, ‘Master, your mina has made five minas. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And to this one he said, ‘You shall have authority over five cities. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Then another servant came and said, ‘Master, here is your mina, which I have laid away in a piece of cloth.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["soudari&#333;"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"For I was afraid of you, because you are a harsh man. You withdraw what you did not deposit and reap what you did not sow. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"His master replied, ‘You wicked servant, I will judge you by your own words. So you knew that I am a harsh man, withdrawing what I did not deposit and reaping what I did not sow?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Why then did you not deposit my money in the bank, and upon my return I could have collected it with interest? ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then he told those standing by, ‘Take the mina from him and give it to the one who has ten minas. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"‘Master,’ they said, ‘he already has ten! ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"He replied, ‘ I tell you that everyone who has will be given more; but the one who does not have, even what he has will be taken away from him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And these enemies of mine who were unwilling for me to rule over them, bring them here and slay them in front of me..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Triumphal Entry"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Zechariah 9:9–13; Matthew 21:1–11; Mark 11:1–11; John 12:12–19)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"After Jesus had said this, He went on ahead, going up to Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"As He approached Bethphage and Bethany at the Mount of Olives, He sent out two of His disciples,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go into the village ahead of you, and as you enter it, you will find a colt tied there, on which no one has ever sat. Untie it and bring it here.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"If anyone asks, ‘Why are you untying it?’ tell him, ‘The Lord needs it..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"So those who were sent went out and found it just as Jesus had told them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"As they were untying the colt, its owners asked, “Why are you untying the colt?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"“The Lord needs it,” they answered.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Then they led the colt to Jesus, threw their cloaks over it, and put Jesus on it."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"As He rode along, the people spread their cloaks on the road.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"And as He approached the descent from the Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of disciples began to praise God joyfully in a loud voice for all the miracles they had seen:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"“Blessed is the King who comes in the name of the Lord!”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 118:26"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Peace in heaven and glory in the highest!”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 148:1"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"But some of the Pharisees in the crowd said to Him, “Teacher, rebuke Your disciples!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"“I tell you,” He answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“if they remain silent, the very stones will cry out.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Weeps over Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 29:1–16)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"As Jesus approached Jerusalem and saw the city, He wept over it",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“If only you had known on this day what would bring you peace! But now it is hidden from your eyes.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"For the days will come upon you when your enemies will barricade you and surround you and hem you in on every side.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"They will level you to the ground—you and the children within your walls. They will not leave one stone on another, because you did not recognize the time of your visitation from God.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["your visitation"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Cleanses the Temple"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 21:12–17; Mark 11:15–19; John 2:12–25)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Then Jesus entered the temple courts",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:45"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the temple"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and began to drive out those who were selling there.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"He declared to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“It is written: ‘My house will be a house of prayer.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:46"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 56:7"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"But you have made it ‘a den of robbers.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["19:46"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Jeremiah 7:11"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"Jesus was teaching at the temple every day, but the chief priests, scribes, and leaders of the people were intent on killing Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"Yet they could not find a way to do so, because all the people hung on His words."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus’ Authority Challenged"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 21:23–27; Mark 11:27–33)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"One day as Jesus was teaching the people in the temple courts",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the temple"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and proclaiming the gospel, the chief priests and scribes, together with the elders, came up to Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"“Tell us,” they said, “by what authority are You doing these things, and who gave You this authority?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I will also ask you a question,” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Tell Me:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"John’s baptism—was it from heaven, or from men?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"They deliberated among themselves and said, “If we say, ‘From heaven,’He will ask, ‘Why did you not believe him? ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"But if we say, ‘From men,’all the people will stone us, for they are convinced that John was a prophet.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"So they answered that they did not know where it was from."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"And Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Neither will I tell you by what authority I am doing these things.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Parable of the Wicked Tenants"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 21:33–46; Mark 12:1–12)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Then He proceeded to tell the people this parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“A man planted a vineyard, rented it out to some tenants, and went away for a long time.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"At harvest time, he sent a servant to the tenants to collect his share of the fruit of the vineyard. But the tenants beat the servant and sent him away empty-handed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"So he sent another servant, but they beat him and treated him shamefully, sending him away empty-handed."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Then he sent a third, but they wounded him and threw him out."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"‘What shall I do? ’ asked the owner of the vineyard. ‘I will send my beloved son. Perhaps they will respect him. ’"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"But when the tenants saw the son, they discussed it among themselves and said, ‘This is the heir. Let us kill him, and the inheritance will be ours. ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"So they threw him out of the vineyard and killed him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["What then will the owner of the vineyard do to them?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"He will come and kill those tenants and give the vineyard to others.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And when the people heard this, they said, “May such a thing never happen!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"But Jesus looked directly at them and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Then what is the meaning of that which is written:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘The stone the builders rejected"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["has become the cornerstone ’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:17"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 118:22"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Everyone who falls on this stone will be broken to pieces, but he on whom it falls will be crushed.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Paying Taxes to Caesar"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 22:15–22; Mark 12:13–17)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"When the scribes and chief priests realized that Jesus had spoken this parable against them, they sought to arrest Him that very hour. But they were afraid of the people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"So they watched Him closely and sent spies who pretended to be sincere. They were hoping to catch Him in His words in order to hand Him over to the rule and authority of the governor.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"“Teacher,” they inquired, “we know that You speak and teach correctly. You show no partiality but teach the way of God in accordance with the truth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Is it lawful for us to pay taxes to Caesar or not?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But Jesus saw through their duplicity and said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"“Show Me a denarius.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:24"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A denarius was customarily a day’s wage for a laborer; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 20:2"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"Whose image and inscription are on it?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Caesar’s,” they answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"So Jesus told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Give to Caesar what is Caesar’s, and to God what is God’s.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"And they were unable to trap Him in His words before the people. And amazed at His answer, they fell silent."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Sadducees and the Resurrection"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 22:23–33; Mark 12:18–27)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"Then some of the Sadducees, who say there is no resurrection, came to question Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"“Teacher,” they said, “Moses wrote for us that if a man’s brother dies and leaves a wife but no children, the man is to marry his brother’s widow and raise up offspring for him.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:28"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Deuteronomy 25:5"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Now there were seven brothers. The first one married a wife but died childless.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"Then the second",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:30"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["married the widow, and he also died,"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"and the third married the widow, and in the same way all seven died, leaving no children.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"And last of all, the woman died.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"So then, in the resurrection, whose wife will she be? For all seven were married to her.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The sons of this age marry and are given in marriage.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"But those who are considered worthy to share in the age to come and in the resurrection from the dead will neither marry nor be given in marriage.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"In fact, they can no longer die, because they are like the angels. And since they are sons of the resurrection, they are sons of God."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Even Moses demonstrates that the dead are raised, in the passage about the burning bush. For he calls the Lord ‘the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:37"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 3:6"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"He is not the God of the dead, but of the living, for to Him all are alive.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Some of the scribes answered, “Teacher, You have spoken well!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"And they did not dare to question Him any further."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Whose Son Is the Christ?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 22:41–46; Mark 12:35–37)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"Then Jesus declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“How can it be said that the Christ is the Son of David?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"For David himself says in the book of Psalms:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘The Lord said to my Lord,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Sit at My right hand"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"until I make Your enemies"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["a footstool for Your feet.” ’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:43"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 110:1"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Thus David calls Him ‘Lord.’ So how can He be David’s son?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Beware of the Scribes"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 12:38–40)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"In the hearing of all the people, Jesus said to His disciples,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"“Beware of the scribes. They like to walk around in long robes, and they love the greetings in the marketplaces, the chief seats in the synagogues, and the places of honor at banquets.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"They defraud widows of their houses,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:47"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["They devour widows’ houses"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and for a show make lengthy prayers. These men will receive greater condemnation.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Poor Widow’s Offering"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 12:41–44)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then Jesus looked up and saw the rich putting their gifts into the treasury,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and He saw a poor widow put in two small copper coins.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:2"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["two lepta"]},"; a lepton was a Jewish coin of bronze or copper worth about 1/128 of a denarius."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"“Truly I tell you,” He said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“this poor widow has put in more than all the others.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"For they all contributed out of their surplus, but she out of her poverty has put in all she had to live on.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Temple Destruction and Other Signs"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:1–8; Mark 13:1–8)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"As some of the disciples were remarking how the temple was adorned with beautiful stones and consecrated gifts, Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"“As for what you see here, the time will come when not one stone will be left on another; every one will be thrown down.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"“Teacher,” they asked, “when will these things happen? And what will be the sign that they are about to take place?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“See to it that you are not deceived. For many will come in My name, claiming, ‘I am He,’and, ‘The time is near. ’Do not follow them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"When you hear of wars and rebellions, do not be alarmed. These things must happen first, but the end is not imminent.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Witnessing to All Nations"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:9–14; Mark 13:9–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Then He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"There will be great earthquakes, famines, and pestilences in various places, along with fearful sights and great signs from heaven."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"But before all this, they will seize you and persecute you. On account of My name they will deliver you to the synagogues and prisons, and they will bring you before kings and governors.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"This will be your opportunity to serve as witnesses.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"So make up your mind not to worry beforehand how to defend yourselves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"For I will give you speech and wisdom that none of your adversaries will be able to resist or contradict."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"You will be betrayed even by parents and brothers and relatives and friends, and some of you will be put to death.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"And you will be hated by everyone because of My name.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"Yet not even a hair of your head will perish.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"By your patient endurance you will gain your souls."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Destruction of Jerusalem"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:15–25; Mark 13:14–23)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"But when you see Jerusalem surrounded by armies, you will know that her desolation is near.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Then let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains, let those in the city get out, and let those in the country stay out of the city.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"For these are the days of vengeance, to fulfill all that is written."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"How miserable those days will be for pregnant and nursing mothers! For there will be great distress upon the land and wrath against this people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"They will fall by the edge of the sword and be led captive into all the nations. And Jerusalem will be trodden down by the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles are fulfilled."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Return of the Son of Man"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:26–31; Mark 13:24–27)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"There will be signs in the sun and moon and stars, and on the earth dismay among the nations, bewildered by the roaring of the sea and the surging of the waves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Men will faint from fear and anxiety over what is coming upon the earth, for the powers of the heavens will be shaken.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"At that time they will see the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:27"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Daniel 7:13–14"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"When these things begin to happen, stand up and lift up your heads, because your redemption is drawing near.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Lesson of the Fig Tree"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 24:32–35; Mark 13:28–31)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Then Jesus told them a parable:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Look at the fig tree and all the trees.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"When they sprout leaves, you can see for yourselves and know that summer is near.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"So also, when you see these things happening, know that the kingdom of God is near.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Truly I tell you, this generation will not pass away until all these things have happened.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"Heaven and earth will pass away, but My words will never pass away."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Be Watchful for the Day"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"But watch yourselves, or your hearts will be weighed down by dissipation, drunkenness, and the worries of life—and that day will spring upon you suddenly like a snare.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"For it will come upon all who dwell on the face of all the earth.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"So keep watch at all times, and pray that you may have the strength to escape all that is about to happen and to stand before the Son of Man.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"Every day Jesus taught at the temple, but every evening He went out to spend the night on the Mount of Olives.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"And early in the morning all the people would come to hear Him at the temple."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Plot to Kill Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:1–5; Mark 14:1–2; John 11:45–57)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Now the Feast of Unleavened Bread,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the feast of the Unleavened"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Exodus 12:14–20"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"called the Passover, was approaching,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"and the chief priests and scribes were looking for a way to put Jesus to death, for they feared the people."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:14–16; Mark 14:10–11)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"Then Satan entered Judas Iscariot, who was one of the Twelve.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"And Judas went to discuss with the chief priests and temple officers how he might betray Jesus to them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"They were delighted and agreed to give him money.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"Judas consented, and began to look for an opportunity to betray Jesus to them in the absence of a crowd."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Preparing the Passover"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:17–19; Mark 14:12–16)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"Then came the day of Unleavened Bread on which the Passover lamb was to be sacrificed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Jesus sent Peter and John, saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Go and make preparations for us to eat the Passover.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"“Where do You want us to prepare it?” they asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"He answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“When you enter the city, a man carrying a jug of water will meet you. Follow him to the house he enters,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"and say to the owner of that house, ‘The Teacher asks: Where is the guest room, where I may eat the Passover with My disciples? ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"And he will show you a large upper room, already furnished. Make preparations there.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"So they went and found it just as Jesus had told them. And they prepared the Passover."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Last Supper"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:20–30; Mark 14:17–26; 1 Corinthians 11:17–34)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"When the hour had come, Jesus reclined at the table with His apostles.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And He said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I have eagerly desired to eat this Passover with you before My suffering.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"For I tell you that I will not eat it again until it is fulfilled in the kingdom of God.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"After taking the cup, He gave thanks and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Take this and divide it among yourselves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"For I tell you that I will not drink of the fruit of the vine from now on until the kingdom of God comes.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"And He took the bread, gave thanks and broke it, and gave it to them, saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“This is My body, given for you; do this in remembrance of Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"In the same way, after supper He took the cup, saying,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“This cup is the new covenant in My blood, which is poured out for you.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:20"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some manuscripts end verse 19 after ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["This is My body"]},"and do not include verse 20."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"Look! The hand of My betrayer is with Mine on the table.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Indeed, the Son of Man will go as it has been determined, but woe to that man who betrays Him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"Then they began to question among themselves which of them was going to do this."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Who Is the Greatest?"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"A dispute also arose among the disciples as to which of them should be considered the greatest.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"So Jesus declared,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The kings of the Gentiles lord it over them, and those in authority over them call themselves benefactors.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"But you shall not be like them. Instead, the greatest among you should be like the youngest, and the one who leads like the one who serves.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"For who is greater, the one who reclines at the table or the one who serves? Is it not the one who reclines? But I am among you as one who serves."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"You are the ones who have stood by Me in My trials.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"And I bestow on you a kingdom, just as My Father has bestowed one on Me,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"so that you may eat and drink at My table in My kingdom and sit on thrones, judging the twelve tribes of Israel."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Predicts Peter’s Denial"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:31–35; Mark 14:27–31; John 13:36–38)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Simon, Simon, Satan has asked to sift all of you like wheat.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"But I have prayed for you, Simon, that your faith will not fail. And when you have turned back, strengthen your brothers.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"“Lord,” said Peter, “I am ready to go with You even to prison and to death.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"But Jesus replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“I tell you, Peter, the rooster will not crow today until you have denied three times that you know Me.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Then Jesus asked them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“When I sent you out without purse or bag or sandals, did you lack anything?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Nothing,” they answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"“Now, however,” He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“the one with a purse should take it, and likewise a bag; and the one without a sword should sell his cloak and buy one.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"For I tell you that this Scripture must be fulfilled in Me: ‘And He was numbered with the transgressors.’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:37"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Isaiah 53:12"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"For what is written about Me is reaching its fulfillment.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"So they said, “Look, Lord, here are two swords.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“That is enough,” He answered."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Prays on the Mount of Olives"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:36–46; Mark 14:32–42)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Jesus went out as usual to the Mount of Olives, and the disciples followed Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"When He came to the place, He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Pray that you will not enter into temptation.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"And He withdrew about a stone’s throw beyond them, where He knelt down and prayed,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Father, if You are willing, take this cup from Me. Yet not My will, but Yours be done.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"Then an angel from heaven appeared to Him and strengthened Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"And in His anguish, He prayed more earnestly, and His sweat became like drops of blood falling to the ground.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some manuscripts do not include verses 43 and 44."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"When Jesus rose from prayer and returned to the disciples, He found them asleep, exhausted from sorrow."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"“Why are you sleeping?” He asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Get up and pray so that you will not enter into temptation.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Betrayal of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:47–56; Mark 14:43–52; John 18:1–14)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"While He was still speaking, a crowd arrived, led by the man called Judas, one of the Twelve. He approached Jesus to kiss Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"But Jesus asked him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Judas, are you betraying the Son of Man with a kiss?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"Those around Jesus saw what was about to happen and said, “Lord, should we strike with our swords?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"And one of them struck the servant of the high priest, cutting off his right ear."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"But Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“No more of this!” And He touched the man’s ear and healed him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"Then Jesus said to the chief priests, temple officers, and elders who had come for Him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Have you come out with swords and clubs as you would against an outlaw?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"Every day I was with you in the temple courts,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:53"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["the temple"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and you did not lay a hand on Me. But this hour belongs to you and to the power of darkness.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Peter Denies Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:69–75; Mark 14:66–72; John 18:15–18)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"Then they seized Jesus, led Him away, and took Him into the house of the high priest. And Peter followed at a distance."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"When those present had kindled a fire in the middle of the courtyard and sat down together, Peter sat down among them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"A servant girl saw him seated in the firelight and looked intently at him. “This man also was with Him,” she said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57"},"But Peter denied it. “Woman, I do not know Him,” he said."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58"},"A short time later, someone else saw him and said, “You also are one of them.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["But Peter said, “Man, I am not.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59"},"About an hour later, another man insisted, “Certainly this man was with Him, for he too is a Galilean.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60"},"“Man, I do not know what you are talking about,” Peter replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["And immediately, while he was still speaking, the rooster crowed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61"},"And the Lord turned and looked at Peter."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then Peter remembered the word that the Lord had spoken to him:"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Before the rooster crows today, you will deny Me three times.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62"},"And he went outside and wept bitterly."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Soldiers Mock Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 50:4–11; Matthew 27:27–31; Mark 15:16–20; John 19:1–15)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63"},"The men who were holding Jesus began to mock Him and beat Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"64"},"They blindfolded Him",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:64"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["and were striking Him on the face"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"and kept demanding, “Prophesy! Who hit You?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"65"},"And they said many other blasphemous things against Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus before the Sanhedrin"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 26:57–68; Mark 14:53–65; John 18:19–24)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"66"},"At daybreak the council of the elders of the people, both the chief priests and scribes, met together. They led Jesus into their Sanhedrin",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:66"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["their Council"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and said,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"67"},"“If You are the Christ, tell us.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Jesus answered,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“If I tell you, you will not believe.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"68"},"And if I ask you a question, you will not answer.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"69"},"But from now on the Son of Man will be seated at the right hand of the power of God.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:69"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 110:1"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"70"},"So they all asked, “Are You then the Son of God?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He replied,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You say that I am.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"71"},"“Why do we need any more testimony?” they declared. “We have heard it for ourselves from His own lips.”"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus before Pilate"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 27:11–14; John 18:28–40)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"Then the whole council rose and led Jesus away to Pilate.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"And they began to accuse Him, saying, “We found this man subverting our nation, forbidding payment of taxes to Caesar, and proclaiming Himself to be Christ, a King.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"So Pilate asked Him, “Are You the King of the Jews?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“You have said so,” Jesus replied."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"Then Pilate said to the chief priests and the crowds, “I find no basis for a charge against this man.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"But they kept insisting, “He stirs up the people all over Judea with His teaching. He began in Galilee and has come all the way here.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus before Herod"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"When Pilate heard this, he asked if the man was a Galilean.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"},"And learning that Jesus was under Herod’s jurisdiction, he sent Him to Herod, who himself was in Jerusalem at that time."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"When Herod saw Jesus, he was greatly pleased. He had wanted to see Him for a long time, because he had heard about Him and was hoping to see Him perform a miracle.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"Herod questioned Jesus at great length, but He gave no answer."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"Meanwhile, the chief priests and scribes stood there, vehemently accusing Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"And even Herod and his soldiers ridiculed and mocked Him. Dressing Him in a fine robe, they sent Him back to Pilate."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"That day Herod and Pilate became friends; before this time they had been enemies."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Crowd Chooses Barabbas"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 27:15–23; Mark 15:6–11)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"Then Pilate called together the chief priests, the rulers, and the people,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"and said to them, “You brought me this man as one who was inciting the people to rebellion. I have examined Him here in your presence and found Him not guilty of your charges against Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"Neither has Herod, for he sent Him back to us. As you can see, He has done nothing deserving of death.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"Therefore I will punish Him and release Him.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:16"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["17Now Pilate was obligated to release to the people one prisoner at the feast"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matthew 27:15"]},"and",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Mark 15:6"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"But they all cried out in unison: “Away with this man! Release Barabbas to us!”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"(Barabbas had been imprisoned for an insurrection in the city, and for murder.)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Wanting to release Jesus, Pilate addressed them again,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"but they kept shouting, “Crucify Him! Crucify Him!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"A third time he said to them, “What evil has this man done? I have found in Him no offense worthy of death. So after I punish Him, I will release Him.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"But they were insistent, demanding with loud voices for Jesus to be crucified. And their clamor",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:23"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["and that of the chief priests"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"prevailed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"So Pilate sentenced that their demand be met.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"As they had requested, he released the one imprisoned for insurrection and murder, and he handed Jesus over to their will."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Crucifixion"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Psalm 22:1–31; Matthew 27:32–44; Mark 15:21–32; John 19:16–27)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"As the soldiers led Him away, they seized Simon of Cyrene on his way in from the country, and they put the cross on him to carry behind Jesus."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"A great number of people followed Him, including women who kept mourning and wailing for Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"But Jesus turned to them and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Daughters of Jerusalem, do not weep for Me, but weep for yourselves and for your children.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"Look, the days are coming when people will say, ‘Blessed are the barren women, the wombs that never bore, and breasts that never nursed! ’",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"At that time"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘ they will say to the mountains, “Fall on us!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["and to the hills, “Cover us!” ’",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:30"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Hosea 10:8"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"For if men do these things while the tree is green, what will happen when it is dry?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"Two others, who were criminals, were also led away to be executed with Jesus."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"When they came to the place called The Skull,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:33"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Kranion"]},"; Vulgate ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Calvariae"]},", rendered in some translations as ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Calvary"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"they crucified Him there, along with the criminals, one on His right and the other on His left."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"Then Jesus said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Father, forgive them, for they do not know what they are doing.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Some manuscripts do not include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["Then Jesus said, “Father... what they are doing.”"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"And they divided up His garments by casting lots.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:34"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 22:18"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"The people stood watching, and the rulers sneered at Him,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:35"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["See",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 22:7"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},"saying, “He saved others; let Him save Himself if He is the Christ of God, the Chosen One.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"The soldiers also mocked Him and came up to offer Him sour wine.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:36"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["to offer Him wine vinegar"]}]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"“If You are the King of the Jews,” they said, “save Yourself!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"Above Him was posted an inscription:",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:38"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["written in Greek, Latin, and Hebrew"]},"; see",{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["John 19:20"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["THIS IS THE KING OF THE JEWS."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"One of the criminals who hung there heaped abuse on Him. “Are You not the Christ?” he said. “Save Yourself and us!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"But the other one rebuked him, saying, “Do you not even fear God, since you are under the same judgment?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"We are punished justly, for we are receiving what our actions deserve. But this man has done nothing wrong.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"Then he said, “Jesus, remember me",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:42"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["said to Jesus, “Remember me, Lord,"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"when You come into Your kingdom!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"And Jesus said to him,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Truly I tell you, today you will be with Me in Paradise.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Death of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Psalm 31:1–24; Matthew 27:45–56; Mark 15:33–41; John 19:28–30)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"It was now about the sixth hour, and darkness came over all the land until the ninth hour.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:44"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["That is, from noon until three in the afternoon"]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"The sun was darkened,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:45"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["failed"]}," or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["was obscured"]},"; BYZ and TR ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["became dark"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"and the veil of the temple was torn down the middle."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"Then Jesus called out in a loud voice,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Father, into Your hands I commit My Spirit.”",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:46"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Psalm 31:5"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"And when He had said this, He breathed His last."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"When the centurion saw what had happened, he gave glory to God, saying, “Surely this was a righteous man.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:47"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["an innocent man"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"And when all the people who had gathered for this spectacle saw what had happened, they returned home beating their breasts.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"But all those who knew Jesus, including the women who had followed Him from Galilee, stood at a distance watching these things."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Burial of Jesus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Isaiah 53:9–12; Matthew 27:57–61; Mark 15:42–47; John 19:38–42)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"Now there was a Council member named Joseph, a good and righteous man,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"who had not consented to their decision or action. He was from the Judean town of Arimathea and was waiting for the kingdom of God.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"He went to Pilate to ask for the body of Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"Then he took it down, wrapped it in a linen cloth, and placed it in a tomb cut into the rock, where no one had yet been laid.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54"},"It was Preparation Day, and the Sabbath was beginning.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["23:54"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Or ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["was about to begin"]}]}],"caller":"+"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55"},"The women who had come with Jesus from Galilee followed, and they saw the tomb and how His body was placed.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56"},"Then they returned to prepare spices and perfumes. And they rested on the Sabbath, according to the commandment."]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24"},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Resurrection"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Matthew 28:1–10; Mark 16:1–8; John 20:1–9)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1"},"On the first day of the week,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:1"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["But on the first of the Sabbaths,"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"very early in the morning, the women came to the tomb, bringing the spices they had prepared.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2"},"They found the stone rolled away from the tomb,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3"},"but when they entered, they did not find the body of the Lord Jesus.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4"},"While they were puzzling over this, suddenly two men in radiant apparel stood beside them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5"},"As the women bowed their faces to the ground in terror, the two men asked them, “Why do you look for the living among the dead?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6"},"He is not here; He has risen! Remember how He told you while He was still in Galilee:",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7"}]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["‘The Son of Man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified, and on the third day rise again..”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8"},"Then they remembered His words.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9"},"And when they returned from the tomb, they reported all these things to the Eleven and to all the others.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10"},"It was Mary Magdalene, Joanna, Mary the mother of James, and the other women with them who told this to the apostles.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11"},"But their words seemed like nonsense to them, and they did not believe the women."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12"},"Peter, however, got up and ran to the tomb. And after bending down and seeing only the linen cloths, he went away, wondering to himself what had happened."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Road to Emmaus"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 16:12–13)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13"},"That same day two of them were going to a village called Emmaus, about seven miles",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:13"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Greek ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["being sixty stadia in distance"]},"; that is, approximately 6.9 miles or 11.1 kilometers"]}],"caller":"+"},"from Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14"},"They were talking with each other about everything that had happened.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15"},"And as they talked and deliberated, Jesus Himself came up and walked along with them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16"},"But their eyes were kept from recognizing Him."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17"},"He asked them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“What are you discussing so intently as you walk along?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They stood still, with sadness on their faces.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18"},"One of them, named Cleopas, asked Him, “Are You the only visitor to Jerusalem who does not know the things that have happened there in recent days?”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19"},"“What things?” He asked."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“The events involving Jesus of Nazareth,” they answered. “This man was a prophet, powerful in speech and action before God and all the people.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20"},"Our chief priests and rulers delivered Him up to the sentence of death, and they crucified Him.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21"},"But we were hoping He was the One who would redeem Israel. And besides all this, it is the third day since these things took place."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22"},"Furthermore, some of our women astounded us. They were at the tomb early this morning,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23"},"but they did not find His body. They came and told us they had seen a vision of angels, who said that Jesus was alive.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24"},"Then some of our companions went to the tomb and found it just as the women had described. But Him they did not see.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25"},"Then Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“O foolish ones, and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken!",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26"},"Was it not necessary for the Christ to suffer these things and then to enter His glory?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27"},"And beginning with Moses and all the Prophets, He explained to them what was written in all the Scriptures about Himself."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28"},"As they approached the village where they were headed, He seemed to be going farther.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29"},"But they pleaded with Him, “Stay with us, for it is nearly evening and the day is almost over.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So He went in to stay with them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30"},"While He was reclining at the table with them, He took bread, spoke a blessing and broke it, and gave it to them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31"},"Then their eyes were opened and they recognized Jesus—and He disappeared from their sight."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32"},"They asked each other, “Were not our hearts burning within us as He spoke with us on the road and opened the Scriptures to us?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33"},"And they got up that very hour and returned to Jerusalem."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["There they found the Eleven and those with them, gathered together",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34"},"and saying, “The Lord has indeed risen and has appeared to Simon!”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35"},"Then the two told what had happened on the road, and how they had recognized Jesus in the breaking of the bread."]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["Jesus Appears to the Disciples"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(John 20:19–23; 1 John 1:1–4)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36"},"While they were describing these events, Jesus Himself stood among them and said,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Peace be with you.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37"},"But they were startled and frightened, thinking they had seen a spirit."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38"},"“Why are you troubled,” Jesus asked,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“and why do doubts arise in your hearts?",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39"},"Look at My hands and My feet. It is I Myself. Touch Me and see—for a spirit does not have flesh and bones, as you see I have.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40"},"And when He had said this, He showed them His hands and feet."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41"},"While they were still in disbelief because of their joy and amazement, He asked them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“Do you have anything here to eat?”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42"},"So they gave Him a piece of broiled fish,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:42"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["BYZ and TR include ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["and some honeycomb"]},"."]}],"caller":"+"},{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43"},"and He took it and ate it in front of them."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44"},"Jesus said to them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“These are the words I spoke to you while I was still with you: Everything must be fulfilled that is written about Me in the Law of Moses, the Prophets, and the Psalms.”",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45"},"Then He opened their minds to understand the Scriptures."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46"},"And He told them,"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“This is what is written: The Christ will suffer and rise from the dead on the third day,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47"},"and in His name repentance and",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["24:47"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["NA, NE, and WH ",{"type":"char","marker":"fq","content":["repentance for"]}]}],"caller":"+"},"forgiveness of sins will be proclaimed to all nations, beginning in Jerusalem.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48"},"You are witnesses of these things."]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49"},"And behold, I am sending the promise of My Father upon you. But remain in the city until you have been clothed with power from on high.”"]},{"type":"para","marker":"s1","content":["The Ascension"]},{"type":"para","marker":"r","content":["(Mark 16:19–20; Acts 1:6–11)"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50"},"When Jesus had led them out as far as Bethany, He lifted up His hands and blessed them.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51"},"While He was blessing them, He left them and was carried up into heaven.",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52"},"And they worshiped Him and returned to Jerusalem with great joy,",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53"},"praising God continually in the temple."]}]}